DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field is the full date and time of a call. During use in a summary report, this field is grouped to the nearest hour with a format of m/d/yyyy h:00:00. If you add this as a row or column to a summary report, you will see activity grouped by day and hour.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: This field is your primary filter field for date range. Use this field as a filter to select a date range for your report even if you won't be including this field on the report. In addition, use this field on your report if you want your data grouped by calendar date and hour.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call End Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the same as Call Date/Time except it marks the end of the call.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Extension
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the ShoreTel extension being reported.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: While you can report on extension, people often find it easier to report on Party Name instead. Both are available for your convenience.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field is used to break out calls into different types. Examples of types are ExttoExt, Inbound, Outbound, or Tandem

DimensionTooltips.Name: Party Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the name assigned to the extension that you are reporting on.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: The Party name is usually more meaningful to report on the the Extension, but both are available for your convenience.

DimensionTooltips.Name: DID/DNIS
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the direct number dialed by the outside party on an inbound call.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Workgroup Call
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field indicates the number of Workgroup vs Non-Workgroup calls. Workgroup calls will be designated as WG and Non-Workgroup calls will be Non-WG.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can add this field to a report to note calls that are or are not workgroup calls, or you can add this as a filter to look at calls that are only workgroup calls or non-workgroup calls.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Account Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: If account codes are enabled, this will show the account code, if any, that the caller used to place the call.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: Account Codes are generally used for billing -- to apply the billable minutes of a call to a particular client.  They can also be used as passwords for external or long-distance call permissions.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Account Code Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: If account codes are enabled, this will show the name of the account code, if any, that the caller used to place the call.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: Account Codes are generally used for billing -- to apply the billable minutes of a call to a particular client.  They can also be used as passwords for external or long-distance call permissions.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Spoke To Person
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For inbound calls, whether the caller eventually spoke to a person or not.  Outbound and internal calls show as n/a.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: This is mainly used as a filter for the 'Time To First Person' value, so that calls that never went to a person do not factor in to the averages.  However it can also be good for showing a breakdown of how many calls end up getting to a person vs how many do not.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Long Distance
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For outbound calls, whether the call was Local, Long Distance (LD), or International (Intl).  Does not apply to Inbound or Internal (ExtToExt) calls.

DimensionTooltips.Name: User Group
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The user group to which the user who made or received the call belongs.  In the case of Tandem calls, in which no user is involved, this will show the trunk group originating the call leg.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Country Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The country code of the caller, for external inbound calls on which CallerID is available.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Area Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The area code of the caller, for external inbound calls on which CallerID is available.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: This is currently only supported for calls from North America, UK, Australia, and New Zealand.  Every country has their own format for area/region codes according to their numbering plan.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show calls grouped by hour of the day. If you want calls grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Weekday
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the day of the week (Sunday - Saturday)
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the calls for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. calls for Wednesday in week 1 and calls for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together for a total number of calls on Wednesdays.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the calls for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. calls for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of calls under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group calls by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by month of the year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by week

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year-Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The year and month together as a single value
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: Good for grouping data by month in sequential order

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the phone number of the party that placed the call. Note that for an outbound or ext-to-ext call, this field is populated with the extension of the internal party that placed the call.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Action
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the Connect Reason from the ShoreTel database. It represents the reason the user is on the call. It includes fields like Called, Originate, Redirect, Transfer, etc. This is only available in Detailed reports.
DetailDimensionTooltips.UseTip: While this data may be helpful in certain circumstances, it is often easier to use Call Type instead.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Trunk
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For external calls, this is the trunk line on which the call was made.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Dialed Number
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field is the dialed number, regardless of type of call. For an inbound call, this is the same as the DID/DNIS field. For an Outbound call, this is the number dialed by the ShoreTel user, and for Ext-to-Ext calls this is the extension to which the call was placed.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Long Distance (detail)
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call was long distance or not.  'LD' means long distance, otherwise this field will be blank.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Note
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Any call notes added to the call by users.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Caller ID Name
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name, if any, associated with the caller ID.
DetailDimensionTooltips.UseTip: For ExtToExt and Outbound calls this will be the same as the party name, but for Inbound or Tandem calls it will be the name provided with the trunk call, if the service on the trunk supports passing the CallerID name

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Trunk Group
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The trunk group for inbound or outbound calls.  In the case of Tandem calls this will show the outgoing trunk group.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Call GUID
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The call GUID uniquely identifying this call throughout the ShoreTel system.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Duration
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represent the length of the calls being reported
FactTooltips.UseTip: In a summary report this represents the total duration of all calls reported. In a detail report, this represents the length of each individual call being reported.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the number of calls being reported and is only available on a summary report.

FactTooltips.Name: Time to First Person
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total time in seconds callers spent in the phone system before speaking to a person.
FactTooltips.UseTip: This value is useful on detail reports, but for summary reports the average time to first person is probably more useful

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Call Duration
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Average Call Duration is a measure of total call duration / number of calls and is only available on summary reports

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Time to First Person
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Average time callers spent in the phone system before speaking to a person.

DetailFactTooltips.Name: Party Count
DetailFactTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of parties involved in this call.
DetailFactTooltips.UseTip: Especially useful for abandoned calls to see how many steps the caller went through before they abandoned the call.

DataSourceTooltip.Name: ShoreTel Call Data
DataSourceTooltip.Tooltip: This data source represents each call in the ShoreTel system, along with data about that call.
DataSourceTooltip.UseTip: Use this data source if you want reports around calls.  In particular, note that since each call is represented only once, the ShoreTel system makes a best guess at the user to associate with the call.  For outbound calls, the user who places the call is represented as the internal party (extension and party name).  For inbound calls, the last person to be added to the call is represented as the internal party.  This data is not an accurate indicator of call activity by a user.  For example, if a call comes in to the main number and a receptionist answers, talks to the caller, then transfers the call to person B, person B will be recorded as the party who received the call, not the receptionist.  And the entire length of the call will be reported for person B, which includes the receptionist's time as well.  Hence this data source should only be used for overall call data, such as how many calls are received to a particular DID, or come in during business hours, and should not be considered an accurate representation of an individual user's activity.  For that, see 'Call Party Activity' instead.

Dimensions.Name: Call Date/Time
Dimensions.SourceColumn: qc.starttime

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Abandon}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:ForwardBusy}}', '{{2:FwdNoLoginAgent}}', '{{2:ForwardAlways}}') THEN NULL ELSE Fact0 END)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Queued - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact1) / SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:FwdNoLoginAgent}}' THEN NULL WHEN '{{2:ForwardAlways}}' THEN NULL ELSE Fact0 END)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Agent - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact2) / SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted = '{{3:Agent}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Agent Transferred
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(Fact3) / SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted = '{{3:Agent}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END)

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Abandoned
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Abandon}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Handled by Agent
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted = '{{3:Agent}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Handled by WG Voicemail
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim3.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{3:Mailbox}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Queue Transfer
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:TransferExtensi}}' THEN Fact0 WHEN '{{2:TransferMenu}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Queue Overflow/Interflow
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Overflow}}' THEN Fact0 WHEN '{{2:Interflow}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Handled by Others
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:TransferExtensi}}', '{{2:TransferMenu}}', '{{2:Overflow}}', '{{2:Interflow}}', '{{2:Abandon}}') OR dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:Agent}}', '{{3:Mailbox}}') THEN 0 ELSE Fact0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Abandoned Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Abandon}}' THEN Fact1 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Abandon}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Handled Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact2 + Fact6) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:Agent}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Handled by Agent
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:Agent}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg - # of agents logged in
CalculatedFields.Expression: ROUND(SUM(Fact5) / NULLIF(COUNT(DISTINCT CONCAT(Dimension0, Dimension1)) * 60, 0), 2)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg - # of calls in queue
CalculatedFields.Expression: ROUND(SUM(Fact1) / NULLIF(COUNT(DISTINCT Dimension0) * 60, 0), 2)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Handled by WG Voicemail
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE dim3.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{3:Mailbox}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Wrapup Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact6) / SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:Agent}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Queue Transfer
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:TransferExtensi}}' THEN Fact0 WHEN '{{2:TransferMenu}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Queue Overflow/Interflow
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Overflow}}' THEN Fact0 WHEN '{{2:Interflow}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:FwdNoLoginAgent}}' THEN NULL WHEN '{{2:ForwardAlways}}' THEN NULL ELSE Fact0 END)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Handled by Others
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:TransferExtensi}}', '{{2:TransferMenu}}', '{{2:Overflow}}', '{{2:Interflow}}', '{{2:Abandon}}') OR dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:Mailbox}}', '{{3:Agent}}') THEN 0 ELSE Fact0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Agent Talk - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact7) / SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:Agent}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Agent Hold - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact8) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact9), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Queued Calls
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:ForwardBusy}}', '{{2:FwdNoLoginAgent}}', '{{2:ForwardAlways}}') THEN 0 ELSE Fact0 END

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 1 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102) + ' - ' + convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 7 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Queued
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:ForwardBusy}}', '{{2:FwdNoLoginAgent}}', '{{2:ForwardAlways}}') THEN 'Not Queued' ELSE 'Queued' END

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year-Month
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: CONCAT(DATENAME(yy, Dimension0), '-', RIGHT(CONCAT('0', CAST(DATEPART(mm, Dimension0) AS nvarchar)), 2))

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field is the full date and time of a call. During use in a summary report, this field is grouped to the nearest hour with a format of m/d/yyyy h:00:00. If you add this as a row or column to a summary report, you will see activity grouped by day and hour.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: This field is your primary filter field for date range. Use this field as a filter to select a date range for your report even if you won't be including this field on the report. In addition, use this field on your report if you want your data grouped by calendar date and hour.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Workgroup Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the name of the Workgroup Queue
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: Filter on this report to restrict reports to individual Workgroups

DimensionTooltips.Name: Exit Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the reason that the call left the workgroup Queue. Possible values are Abandon, ForwardAlways, ForwardBusy, ForwardMaxRings, ForwardNoAnswer, FwdNoLoginAgent, Interflow, Overflow, Pickup, Reserved, TransferExtension, TransferMenu, TransferToAgent, TransferVM, Unpark
DimensionTooltips.UseTip:
Abandoned = The caller hung up while waiting in the workgroup queue 
ForwardAlways = The call came in while the workgroup was in a call handling mode that immediately forwards all calls (e.g. off-hours) 
ForwardBusy = The call was forwarded by the workgroup because all logged-in agents were busy 
ForwardMaxRings = The call was forwarded by the workgroup because the maximum number of rings was reached before an agent was found 
ForwardNoAnswer = The call was forwarded by the workgroup because all available agents did not answer 
FwdNoLoginAgent = The call was forwarded by the workgroup because no agents were logged in 
Interflow = The call interflowed to another destination per the last queue step configuration 
Overflow = The call overflowed to another workgroup per the last queue step configuration 
Reserved = The workgroup service was unable to identify why the call left the workgroup 
Pickup = The call was removed from queue via Pickup 
TransferExtension = The caller chose an option to exit the workgroup queue that took them to another extension 
TransferMenu = The caller chose an option to exit the workgroup queue that took them to an AA menu 
TransferToAgent = The call was answered by a workgroup agent 
TransferVM = The caller chose an option to exit the workgroup queue and go to voicemail 
Unpark = Call was removed from queue via Unpark

DimensionTooltips.Name: Target Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the type of target that the call was routed to out of the Workgroup queue. Possible values are Agent, Menu, Mailbox, OtherIntrnExtrn
DimensionTooltips.UseTip:
Agent = Call was transferred to a Workgroup Agent
Menu = Call was transferred to an auto-attendant menu
Mailbox = Call was transferred to a Voicemail
OtherIntrnExtrn =  Call was transferred to another destination, either internal to the ShoreTel system or external

DimensionTooltips.Name: Party Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the Workgroup Agent on the report

DimensionTooltips.Name: Wait Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The wait time histogram -- calls are grouped from 0 to 2 minutes in 30 second intervals, then 2-10 minutes in 1-minute intervals, then all calls queued 10 minutes or more

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The call type: Inbound, Outbound, or ExtToExt (Internal)

DimensionTooltips.Name: Workgroup Extension
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the extension of the Workgroup as configured in Director
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this to filter your workgroups if you know them by extension better than name, or if your workgroups are grouped by extension ranges and you want to use a Range filter instead of Multiple filter.

DimensionTooltips.Name: DID/DNIS
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The DID/DNIS on which the call came in.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Country Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The country code of the caller, if CallerID is available.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Area Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The area code of the caller, if CallerID is available.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: Only North America, UK, Australia, and New Zealand phone numbers are supported at this time.  Every country has their own conventions for area/region codes within their numbering plan.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show calls grouped by hour of the day. If you want calls grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the calls for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. calls for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of calls under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group calls by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by month of the year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by week

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Queued
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call was a queued call or not.  Calls with an exit reason of 'ForwardAlways' or 'FwdNoLoginAgent' are calls that were not queued, and as such do not factor in the queue performance metrics like percentage of abandoned calls or average queue time.  All other exit reasons, such as TransferToAgent, Abandoned, ForwardBusy, etc, are considered calls that were queued.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year-Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The year and month together as a single value
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: Good for grouping data by month in sequential order

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the phone number of the party that placed the call. Note that for an outbound call, this field is populated with the extension of the internal party that placed the call.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Transfer Destination
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Extension or destination that the call was transferred to by the agent, if they did so.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID Name
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name, if any, associated with the caller ID.
DetailDimensionTooltips.UseTip: For ExtToExt and Outbound calls this will be the same as the party name, but for Inbound or Tandem calls it will be the name provided with the trunk call, if the service on the trunk supports passing the CallerID name

FactTooltips.Name: Count - All Calls
FactTooltips.Tooltip: Total # of Calls in the given filter set

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Queued - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: All Queue Hold Time during the given time period, added together

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Agent - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: All Agent call time during the given time period, added together

FactTooltips.Name: Count - Agent Transferred
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This is the # of Workgroup calls that the agent transferred to another destination during the given time period

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Queued - Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum queue hold time during the given period.

FactTooltips.Name: Total Login Time
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total agent login time for the given time period and group.  If, for example, four agents are logged in to a group for one hour the total login time for that group for that hour is 240 minutes (60 minutes times four agents)
FactTooltips.UseTip: This field can be used on its own as a measurement if how many agents are servicing the group, but it is also used to calculate the average number of logged in agents.  Make sure when using this value you are not also breaking rows or columns out by exit reason, target type, or other non-time- or workgroup-related dimension, otherwise the totals will not add up correctly.

FactTooltips.Name: Total Wrapup Time
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total time agents spent in wrap-up mode handling calls in this workgroup.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Agent Talk - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: Total talk time by agents answering calls from this queue
FactTooltips.UseTip: 'Time - Agent - Total' is divided into 'Time - Agent Talk - Total' and 'Time - Agent Hold - Total' for those who need more granular reporting on agent talk vs hold times.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Agent Hold - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: Total hold time by agents answering calls from this queue
FactTooltips.UseTip: 'Time - Agent - Total' is divided into 'Time - Agent Talk - Total' and 'Time - Agent Hold - Total' for those who need more granular reporting on agent talk vs hold times.

FactTooltips.Name: Count - Held Calls
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls that agents answered for which there was hold time.  Mainly used for calculating hold percentage and hold average
FactTooltips.UseTip: You will probably not use this field directly, it mainly exists for calculating percent of calls held and average agent hold time.

FactTooltips.Name: Count - Max In Queue
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum number of calls in the corresponding queue at any time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This is the abandon rate as a percentage. This is defined as Abandoned Calls / Workgroup Queued Calls for the given timeperiod

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Queued - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This is the Total Queue Hold Time / Total # of queued calls

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Agent - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average time calls spent with agents answering calls from this queue.  This is total agent call time divided by number of calls that were answered by agents.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: Use this metric to determine how long on average callers spend with agents that handle the calls from this queue.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Agent Transferred
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This is the agent call transfers as a percentage. This is defined as the # of workgroup calls transferred by the agent / the total number of workgroup calls taken by the agent during the given time period.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Abandoned
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Abandoned calls are calls in which the caller hung up while still in the queue

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Handled by Agent
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Calls that have a Target Type of Agent

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Handled by WG Voicemail
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Calls that have a target type of 'Mailbox'

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Queue Transfer
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Calls that have the exit reason TransferExtension or TransferMenu

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Queue Overflow/Interflow
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Calls that have the exit reason Interflow or Overflow

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Handled by Others
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: All Calls that do not have one of the following exit reasons: TransferToAgent, Unpark, TransferVM, Interflow, Overflow, TransferExtension, or TransferMenu

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Abandoned Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The Average Abandon Time is the average time that callers held before hanging up while still in the queue during the given time period.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Handled Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This is the Total Agent Time (Talk plus Hold) plus Total Wrap-up Time / Total # of calls that were transferred to agent
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: Use this field if you want to see the average time agents spend handling calls in this group, including talk time, hold time, and wrap-up time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Handled by Agent
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Percent of calls that have the exit reason of TransferToAgent or Unpark

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg - # of agents logged in
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average number of agents logged-in to the group over the time period.  This is calculated by dividing the total login minutes by the total minutes in the report time period.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg - # of calls in queue
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average number of calls waiting in the queue at any given time.  This is calculated by dividing the total number of queue minutes by the total minutes in the report time period.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Handled by WG Voicemail
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Percent of calls that have a target type of 'Mailbox'

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Wrapup Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Average time agents spend in wrap-up time per call they handle from this workgroup.  This is the total wrap-up time divided by number of calls answered by agents.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Queue Transfer
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Percent of calls that have the exit reason TransferExtension or TransferMenu

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Queue Overflow/Interflow
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Percent of QUEUED calls that have the exit reason Interflow or Overflow

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Handled by Others
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Percent of calls that do not have one of the following exit reasons: TransferToAgent, Unpark, TransferVM, Interflow, Overflow, TransferExtension, or TransferMenu

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Agent Talk - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average talk time for agents answering calls from this queue.  Note that this is different from Time - Agent - Avg because that value measures the total time the call is with the agent, whereas this value measures only the talk time (i.e. hold time is excluded).
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: If agent talk time and/or agent hold time is important to your organization's metrics, you may wish to include this value and 'Time - Agent Hold - Avg' instead of or in addition to 'Time - Agent - Avg'.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Agent Hold - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average time that calls agents put on hold spent on hold.  Specifically this is the total hold time divided by number of calls *that were put on hold*.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: If agent talk time and/or agent hold time is important to your organization's metrics, you may wish to include this value and 'Time - Agent Talk - Avg' instead of or in addition to 'Time - Agent - Avg'.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Queued Calls
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were accepted and queued to the workgroup.  This does not mean the caller experienced any queue steps such as hold music, simply that the call was accepted by the workgroup for distribution to agents.  Calls are not queued if they follow a 'Forward Always', 'Busy', or 'No Agents Logged In' call handling rule that is configured to do something other than queue the call.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is the value that is the denominator for many percentages such as '% Abandoned' and '% Overflow/Interflow'

DetailFactTooltips.Name: Count - Transfers
DetailFactTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number of parties after the initial agent who were involved in the call.  All party types that had talk time are represented (e.g. employees, auto-attendants, voicemail boxes)

DataSourceTooltip.Name: ShoreTel Queue Data
DataSourceTooltip.Tooltip: This data source represents calls associated to workgroups.
DataSourceTooltip.UseTip: Use this data source if you want reports around inbound workgroup call data.

Dimensions.SourceColumn: cn.connecttime

Dimensions.Name: Disconnect Reason
Dimensions.SourceColumn: disconnectreason.name

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Duration
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact3) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact2), 0)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 1 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102) + ' - ' + convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 7 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102)

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The date and time that the trunk was utilized.  For summary reports this groups the usage by hour for the time range selected.  For detail reports it will list the start time of each trunk utilization record.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Trunk Group
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The trunk group of the utilized trunks (e.g. 'Analog Loop Start')

DimensionTooltips.Name: Trunk (do not use)
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The individual trunk utilized (e.g. 'PRI (3)')

DimensionTooltips.Name: Direction
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The direction in which the trunk was used (Inbound or Outbound)

DimensionTooltips.Name: Long Distance
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call was long distance or not

DimensionTooltips.Name: Disconnect Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The ShoreTel DisconnectReason from the trunk.  Typically 'Normal' meaning the ShoreTel system ended the call (e.g. an internal user hung up) or 'HangUp', meaning the trunk ended the call (e.g. the outside caller hung up).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Answered
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether there was talk time on the trunk ('Answered') or no talk time ('Not Answered').  This does not necessarily mean a person was on the line, merely that the trunk was connected and accumulated connected ('talk) time.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show calls grouped by hour of the day. If you want calls grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Weekday
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the day of the week (Sunday - Saturday)
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the calls for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. calls for Wednesday in week 1 and calls for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together for a total number of calls on Wednesdays.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the calls for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. calls for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of calls under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group calls by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by month of the year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by week

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Dialed Number
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The number that was dialed by the caller to use this trunk.
DetailDimensionTooltips.UseTip: For outbound trunk usage this is the external number to which this trunk was connected, however for inbound trunk usage this is the Dialed Number from the call record of which this trunk is only one leg.  If multiple trunks were involved in the call, for example if another external caller was conferenced in, the Dialed Number for the overall call might not necessarily be the number that was dialed on this particular trunk.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The number of the caller that placed the call over this trunk.
DetailDimensionTooltips.UseTip: For inbound trunk usage this is the external number to which this trunk was connected, however for outbound trunk usage this is the CallerID from the call record of which this trunk is only one leg.  If multiple trunks were involved in the call, for example if another external party was conferenced in, the CallerID for the overall call might not necessarily be the number that placed the call on this particular trunk.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Party Name
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The party of record for the call in which this trunk was used.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Extension
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The extension of record for the call in which this trunk was used.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: External Number
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The phone number associated with the trunk.  For inbound calls this is the CallerID, and for outbound calls this is the number dialed.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: User Group
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The user group corresponding to the party of record for the call in which this trunk was used.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Trunk
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The individual trunk utilized (e.g. PRI (3))

FactTooltips.Name: Min Active
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The minimum number of trunks in use in each trunk group during the specified time range.

FactTooltips.Name: Max Active
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum number of trunks in use in each trunk group during the specified time range.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls in each data point

FactTooltips.Name: Total Duration
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total duration in minutes of calls in each data point

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Duration
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average duration in minutes that the trunks were utilized in each data point.

DetailFactTooltips.Name: Talk Time
DetailFactTooltips.Tooltip: The total time the trunk was in a 'Connected' state, accumulating Talk Time.

DataSourceTooltip.Name: Trunk Activity
DataSourceTooltip.Tooltip: This data set tracks the usage of trunks -- the minimum and maximum number of trunks in use in a trunk group during the time period, how many uses (calls more or less) of each trunk, and the number of minutes of trunk usage.  Note that trunk data can vary somewhat from call data since a trunk may only be involved in part of a call (e.g. transfer) or more than one trunk may be involved in a call (e.g. conference).

Dimensions.Name: Call Date/Time
Dimensions.SourceColumn: starttime

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Minutes - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact1) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: % Packet Loss - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact3) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact2), 0)

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field is the full date and time of a call. During use in a summary report, this field is grouped to the nearest hour with a format of m/d/yyyy h:00:00. If you add this as a row or column to a summary report, you will see activity grouped by day and hour.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Encoding Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The encoding type of the media stream (G711, G729, etc).

DimensionTooltips.Name: IP Address
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The IP address of the device reporting media stream statistics.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Site Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The site at which the user or device endpoint is located.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Remote Site Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The site of the other endpoint of the media stream (could be the same site for intra-site calls).

DimensionTooltips.Name: InterSite
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call was within one site (0) or across sites (1).

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls included in the statistics.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of minutes for all calls represented.

FactTooltips.Name: Packets - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of voice packets represented.

FactTooltips.Name: Packets - Lost
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of voice packets lost out of the total packet count.
FactTooltips.UseTip: Lost voice packets cause voice quality problems when it goes above 1% of the total packet count.

FactTooltips.Name: Jitter - Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum jitter experienced on any one call among the calls represented.
FactTooltips.UseTip: Jitter is a measure of the variance in the arrival time of each voice packet.  If voice packets are not received at a constant rate the ShoreTel devices need to increase the size of their jitter buffer, which results in voice quality problems such as delay and echo.

FactTooltips.Name: % Packet Loss - Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The highest packet loss experienced by any one call among the calls represented.

FactTooltips.Name: Jitter - Avg
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The average jitter across all calls represented.
FactTooltips.UseTip: Jitter is a measure of the variance in the arrival time of each voice packet.  If voice packets are not received at a constant rate the ShoreTel devices need to increase the size of their jitter buffer, which results in voice quality problems such as delay and echo.

FactTooltips.Name: Blocked Calls
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were blocked by admission control bandwidth limits.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length per call of the calls represented.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: % Packet Loss - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average packet loss experienced across all calls represented.

DetailFactTooltips.Name: Overruns
DetailFactTooltips.Tooltip: The count of overruns as reported by media stream statistics

DetailFactTooltips.Name: Underruns
DetailFactTooltips.Tooltip: The count of underruns as reported by media stream statistics

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Workgroup
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact4) + SUM(Fact5)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - InB Non-WG
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact11) + SUM(Fact12)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Outbound
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact9) + SUM(Fact10)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Minutes - Workgroup
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact6) + SUM(Fact7)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Minutes - InB Non-WG
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact15) + SUM(Fact16)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Minutes - Outbound
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact13) + SUM(Fact14)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - All Internal
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact4) + SUM(Fact9) + SUM(Fact11)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - All External
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact5) + SUM(Fact10) + SUM(Fact12)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - All Calls
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact9) + SUM(Fact10) + SUM(Fact11) + SUM(Fact12) + SUM(Fact4) + SUM(Fact5)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Minutes - All Internal
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact6) + SUM(Fact13) + SUM(Fact15)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Minutes - All External
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact7) + SUM(Fact14) + SUM(Fact16)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Minutes - All Calls
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact13) + SUM(Fact14) + SUM(Fact15) + SUM(Fact16) + SUM(Fact6) + SUM(Fact7)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - Workgroup Internal
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact6) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact4), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - Workgroup External
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact7) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact5), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - Workgroup Calls
CalculatedFields.Expression: (SUM(Fact6) + SUM(Fact7)) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact4) + SUM(Fact5), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - InB Non-WG Internal
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact15) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact11), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - InB Non-WG External
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact16) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact12), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - Out Internal
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact13) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact9), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - Out External
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact14) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact10), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - InB Non-WG Calls
CalculatedFields.Expression: (SUM(Fact15) + SUM(Fact16)) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact11) + SUM(Fact12), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - Out Calls
CalculatedFields.Expression: (SUM(Fact13) + SUM(Fact14)) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact9) + SUM(Fact10), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - All Internal
CalculatedFields.Expression: (SUM(Fact6) + SUM(Fact13) + SUM(Fact15)) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact4) + SUM(Fact9) + SUM(Fact11), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - All External
CalculatedFields.Expression: (SUM(Fact7) + SUM(Fact14) + SUM(Fact16)) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact5) + SUM(Fact10) + SUM(Fact12), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Minutes - All Calls
CalculatedFields.Expression: (SUM(Fact13) + SUM(Fact14) + SUM(Fact15) + SUM(Fact16) + SUM(Fact6) + SUM(Fact7)) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact9) + SUM(Fact10) + SUM(Fact11) + SUM(Fact12) + SUM(Fact4) + SUM(Fact5), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: % Workgroup Calls Answered
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact17) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact8), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: % Available Time
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * (SUM(Fact0) - (SUM(Fact2) + SUM(Fact3) + SUM(Fact13) + SUM(Fact14) + SUM(Fact15) + SUM(Fact16) + SUM(Fact6) + SUM(Fact7))) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg WG Call Treatment Time
CalculatedFields.Expression: (SUM(Fact2) + SUM(Fact3) + SUM(Fact6) + SUM(Fact7)) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact4) + SUM(Fact5), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Total Wrap-Up
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact2) + SUM(Fact3)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Call Wrap-Up Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact2) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact4) + SUM(Fact5), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Total Available
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact0) - (SUM(Fact2) + SUM(Fact3) + SUM(Fact13) + SUM(Fact14) + SUM(Fact15) + SUM(Fact16) + SUM(Fact6) + SUM(Fact7))

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 1 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102) + ' - ' + convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 7 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year-Month
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: CONCAT(DATENAME(yy, Dimension0), '-', RIGHT(CONCAT('0', CAST(DATEPART(mm, Dimension0) AS nvarchar)), 2))

Use this field as a filter to select a date range for your report even if you won't be including this field on the report. In addition, use this field on your report if you want your data grouped by calendar date and hour.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Extension

DimensionTooltips.Name: Workgroup Extension
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the Extension of the Workgroup Queue

DimensionTooltips.Name: Workgroup Name

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Hour

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show calls grouped by hour of the day. If you want calls grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Weekday

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the calls for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. calls for Wednesday in week 1 and calls for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together  for a total number of calls under Wednesday.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the calls for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. calls for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of calls under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as m/d/yyyy weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group calls by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The month of the year the data represents.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year-Month
