CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: Good for grouping data by month in sequential order

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Activity
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The type of activity being recorded: calls, logins/logouts, non-call wrap-up times

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The calling number for this call, either the external CallerID for inbound calls, or the extension of the caller for outbound and extension to extension calls.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Dialed Number
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The number that was called for this call, either the public phone number for outbound calls, the DID/DNIS for inbound calls, or the extension dialed for extension-to-extension calls.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Reason
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The reason the call was connected to this agent (e.g. TransferToAgent from queue, Transfer from another agent)

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID Name
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name, if any, associated with the caller ID.
DetailDimensionTooltips.UseTip: For ExtToExt and Outbound calls this will be the same as the party name, but for Inbound or Tandem calls it will be the name provided with the trunk call, if the service on the trunk supports passing the CallerID name

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Logged-in
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time during the time period that the agent was logged into any workgroup.  If agents do not use the login/logout functionality and are essentially always logged in, then this will only reflect the hours in which there was call activity.  For example, if an agent logs in in the morning and logs out in the evening, perhaps with logouts during the day for breaks, this will reflect the actual duration of their total login for that day.  However, if an agent never logs out and is essentially logged in from midnight to midnight, this won't show 24 hours but rather the hours in which they were active -- so if they had call activity (any activity, not just workgroup calls) during the 8am, 9am, and 10am hours, this will show 3 hours of login time.  The results may be surprising if agents usually do login and logout but an agent forgets to logout one evening.  They might show 16 hours of login time for that day (login time until midnight).  The following day may show more or less login time than usual depending on their activity.
FactTooltips.UseTip: Use this field if you are not reporting on a specific workgroup and not breaking the report out by workgroup. Otherwise use the 'Time - Logged-in (per-workgroup)' field.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Logged-in (per-workgroup)
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time during the time period that the agent was logged into each workgroup.  If agents do not use the login/logout functionality and are essentially always logged in, then this will only reflect the hours in which there was call activity.  For example, if an agent logs in in the morning and logs out in the evening, perhaps with logouts during the day for breaks, this will reflect the actual duration of their total login for that day.  However, if an agent never logs out and is essentially logged in from midnight to midnight, this won't show 24 hours but rather the hours in which they were active -- so if they had call activity (any activity, not just workgroup calls) during the 8am, 9am, and 10am hours, this will show 3 hours of login time.  The results may be surprising if agents usually do login and logout but an agent forgets to logout one evening.  They might show 16 hours of login time for that day (login time until midnight).  The following day may show more or less login time than usual depending on their activity.
FactTooltips.UseTip: Use this field if you are reporting on a specific workgroup or breaking the report out by workgroup. Otherwise use the 'Time - Logged-in' field.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Call Wrap-Up
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the total time that the agent was in wrap-up mode related to a Workgroup Call

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Non-Call Wrap-Up
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the total time that the agent was in wrap-up mode that was not associated with any call.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Workgroup Internal
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of calls received through a workgroup from internal parties.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Workgroup External
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of external calls received through a workgroup. External calls are calls received from outside the ShoreTel system

FactTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - Workgroup Internal
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on calls received through a workgroup from internal parties.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - Workgroup External
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on external calls received through a workgroup. External calls are calls received from outside the ShoreTel system

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Workgroup Presented
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total number of calls presented to the agent's extension by the workgroup during the time period.
FactTooltips.UseTip: This is useful to compare with 'Call Count - Workgroup' to see how many calls the agent answered versus how many they could have answered. It's important to note, however, that there are some valid configurations in which calls answered could be higher than calls presented.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Out Internal
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of internal extension-to-extension calls placed by the agent.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Out External
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of external calls placed by the agent. External calls are calls placed to numbers outside the ShoreTel system

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - InB Non-WG Internal
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of internal extension-to-extension inbound calls not received through a workgroup.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - InB Non-WG External
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of external inbound calls not received through a workgroup. External calls are calls placed to or received from outside the ShoreTel system

FactTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - Out Internal
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on internal extension-to-extension calls placed by the agent.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - Out External
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on external calls placed by the agent. External calls are calls placed to numbers outside the ShoreTel system

FactTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - InB Non-WG Internal
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on internal extension-to-extension inbound calls not received through a workgroup.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - InB Non-WG External
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on external inbound calls not received through a workgroup. External calls are calls placed to or received from outside the ShoreTel system

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Workgroup Answered
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of workgroup calls answered out of the queue by the agent.
FactTooltips.UseTip: The agent who initially takes the call out of the queue is the agent of record for handling that queue call.  If the agent transfers the call to another agent, the call will count as a workgroup call for both agents, but only as a workgroup answered call for the first agent.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - First Login
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This will be the minimum timestamp from all logins for the agent that day.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Last Logout
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This will be the maxium logout timestamp from all logouts for the agent that day.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Workgroup
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of all calls received through a workgroup

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - InB Non-WG
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of all inbound calls not received through a workgroup

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Outbound
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of all calls placed by the agent.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - Workgroup
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on all calls received through a workgroup

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - InB Non-WG
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on all inbound calls not received through a workgroup

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - Outbound
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on all calls placed by the agent.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - All Internal
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of all extension-to-extension internal calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - All External
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of all external calls. External calls are calls placed to or received from outside the ShoreTel system

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - All Calls
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the count of calls of all types answered or placed by the agent during the time period

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - All Internal
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on all extension-to-extension internal calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - All External
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on all external calls. External calls are calls placed to or received from outside the ShoreTel system

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Minutes - All Calls
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the total time spent on calls of all types answered or placed by the agent during the time period

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - Workgroup Internal
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on calls received through a workgroup from internal parties.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - Workgroup External
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on external calls received through a workgroup. External calls are calls received from outside the ShoreTel system

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - Workgroup Calls
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on all calls received through a workgroup

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - InB Non-WG Internal
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on internal extension-to-extension inbound calls not received through a workgroup.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - InB Non-WG External
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on external inbound calls not received through a workgroup. External calls are calls placed to or received from outside the ShoreTel system

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - Out Internal
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on internal extension-to-extension calls placed by the agent.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - Out External
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on external calls placed by the agent. External calls are calls placed to numbers outside the ShoreTel system

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - InB Non-WG Calls
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on all inbound calls not received through a workgroup

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - Out Calls
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on all calls placed by the agent.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - All Internal
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on all extension-to-extension internal calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - All External
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on all external calls. External calls are calls placed to or received from outside the ShoreTel system

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Minutes - All Calls
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent per call on calls of all types answered or placed by the agent during the time period

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: % Workgroup Calls Answered
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the workgroup calls answered as a percentage of workgroup calls presented to the agent.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is useful to see how many calls the agent answered versus how many they could have answered. It's important to note, however, that there are some valid configurations in which this number could be above 100%.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: % Available Time
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the percentage of logged in time that the agent was neither on a call nor in wrap-up.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg WG Call Treatment Time
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the average time spent to handle each workgroup call, including call time and call wrap-up time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Total Wrap-Up
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the total time that the agent was in wrap-up mode regardless of whether wrap-up mode was call initiated or not.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Call Wrap-Up Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the average time the agent was in wrap-up mode related to Workgoup Calls. It is defined as the total amount of Call Wrap-Up time / # of workgroup calls during the period

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Total Available
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Total time that the agent was logged in and not on a call or in wrap-up mode.

DetailFactTooltips.Name: Wrap-Up Minutes
DetailFactTooltips.Tooltip: For workgroup calls and non-call wrap-up, this is the length of the wrap-up time.

DetailFactTooltips.Name: Call Minutes
DetailFactTooltips.Tooltip: For calls, this is the length of the call.

DetailFactTooltips.Name: Queue Minutes
DetailFactTooltips.Tooltip: For workgroup calls, this is the time spent holding in queue.

DetailFactTooltips.Name: Ring Time
DetailFactTooltips.Tooltip: The ring time for NACD calls and for workgroup distribution calls.  ACD calls have no ring time because once the agent answers the distribution call the ACD call is bridged to them as if by consultive transfer.

Dimensions.Name: Call Date/Time
Dimensions.SourceColumn: cn.connecttime

Dimensions.Name: DID/DNIS
Dimensions.ColumnDefinition: CASE calltype when 'Inbound' THEN dialednumber ELSE '' END

Dimensions.Name: Party Type
Dimensions.SourceColumn: partytype.name

Dimensions.Name: Connect Reason
Dimensions.SourceColumn: connectreason.name

Dimensions.Name: Party Name
Dimensions.SourceColumn: concat(cn.partyidname, ' ', cn.partyidlastname)
Dimensions.Proxies: [{"label":"Party Name"},{"label":"Workgroup Membership","dataSourceType":10,"selectionsQuery":"select description from dn where dntypeid = 9 order by description","valuesQuery":"SELECT DISTINCT CONCAT(IFNULL(ta.firstname, ''), ' ', IFNULL(ta.lastname, '')) FROM workgroupmembers m JOIN users ON users.userdn = m.userdn JOIN tabaddresses ta ON ta.addressid = users.addressid JOIN dn wg ON wg.dn = m.workgroupdn WHERE wg.description in ({{filterValues}})"},{"label":"Hunt Group Membership","dataSourceType":10,"selectionsQuery":"select description from dn where dntypeid = 22 order by description","valuesQuery":"SELECT DISTINCT CONCAT(IFNULL(ta.firstname, ''), ' ', IFNULL(ta.lastname, '')) FROM huntgroupmembers h JOIN users ON users.userdn = h.userdn JOIN tabaddresses ta ON ta.addressid = users.addressid JOIN dn hg ON hg.dn = h.huntgroupdn WHERE hg.description in ({{filterValues}})"},{"label":"Site","dataSourceType":10,"selectionsQuery":"select sitename from sites","valuesQuery":"SELECT DISTINCT CONCAT(IFNULL(ta.firstname, ''), ' ', IFNULL(ta.lastname, '')) FROM users JOIN tabaddresses ta ON ta.AddressId = users.AddressId JOIN usercurrentswitch ucw ON ucw.userdn = users.userdn JOIN switches ON switches.switchid = ucw.currentswitchid JOIN switchgroups USING (switchgroupid) JOIN sites USING (siteid) WHERE sites.sitename in ({{filterValues}})"}]

Dimensions.Name: User Group
Dimensions.SourceColumn: cn.groupname

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Call - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact1) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Ring - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact2) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Talk - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact3) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Hold - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact4) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Abandoned
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim9.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{9:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE dim9.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{9:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Abandon - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE dim9.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{9:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact2 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim9.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{9:Abandoned}}' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Overall Abandoned Call Length Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE dim9.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{9:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact5 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim9.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{9:Abandoned}}' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Handled by User
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted = '{{3:WorkgroupAgent}}' THEN Fact0 WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:Station}}', '{{3:Virtual}}') THEN (CASE WHEN dim12.ValueEncrypted = '{{12:Answered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) WHEN dim8.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{8:Station}}', '{{8:Virtual}}', '{{8:WorkgroupAgent}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Forward on Busy
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim9.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{9:ForwardBusy}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - HG/WG Overflow
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim12.ValueEncrypted = '{{12:No Answer}}' AND dim8.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{8:HuntGroups}}', '{{8:Workgroup}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Handled by Others
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim9.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{9:Abandoned}}', '{{9:ForwardBusy}}') THEN 0 WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted = '{{3:WorkgroupAgent}}' THEN 0 WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:Station}}', '{{3:Virtual}}') THEN (CASE WHEN dim12.ValueEncrypted = '{{12:Answered}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact0 END) WHEN dim8.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{8:Station}}', '{{8:Virtual}}', '{{8:WorkgroupAgent}}') THEN 0 WHEN dim12.ValueEncrypted = '{{12:No Answer}}' AND dim8.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{8:HuntGroups}}', '{{8:Workgroup}}', '{{8:VMForward}}') THEN 0 ELSE Fact0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Handled by VM
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim8.ValueEncrypted = '{{8:VMForward}}' AND dim12.ValueEncrypted = '{{12:No Answer}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Next Party - Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact6) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Handled by User
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted = '{{3:WorkgroupAgent}}' THEN Fact0 WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:Station}}', '{{3:Virtual}}') THEN (CASE WHEN dim12.ValueEncrypted = '{{12:Answered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) WHEN dim8.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{8:Station}}', '{{8:Virtual}}', '{{8:WorkgroupAgent}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Forward on Busy
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE dim9.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{9:ForwardBusy}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - HG/WG Overflow
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim12.ValueEncrypted = '{{12:No Answer}}' AND dim8.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{8:HuntGroups}}', '{{8:Workgroup}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Handled by Others
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim9.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{9:Abandoned}}', '{{9:ForwardBusy}}') THEN 0 WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted = '{{3:WorkgroupAgent}}' THEN 0 WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:Station}}', '{{3:Virtual}}') THEN (CASE WHEN dim12.ValueEncrypted = '{{12:Answered}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact0 END) WHEN dim8.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{8:Station}}', '{{8:Virtual}}', '{{8:WorkgroupAgent}}') THEN 0 WHEN dim12.ValueEncrypted = '{{12:No Answer}}' AND dim8.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{8:HuntGroups}}', '{{8:Workgroup}}', '{{8:VMForward}}') THEN 0 ELSE Fact0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Handled by VM
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim12.ValueEncrypted = '{{12:No Answer}}' AND dim8.ValueEncrypted = '{{8:VMForward}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 1 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102) + ' - ' + convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 7 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year-Month
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: CONCAT(DATENAME(yy, Dimension0), '-', RIGHT(CONCAT('0', CAST(DATEPART(mm, Dimension0) AS nvarchar)), 2))

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field is the full date and time of a call. During use in a summary report, this field is grouped to the nearest hour with a format of m/d/yyyy h:00:00. If you add this as a row or column to a summary report, you will see activity grouped by day and hour.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: This field is your primary filter field for date range. Use this field as a filter to select a date range for your report even if you won't be including this field on the report. In addition, use this field on your report if you want your data grouped by calendar date and hour.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field is used to break out calls into different types. Examples of types are ExttoExt, Inbound, Outbound, or Tandem

DimensionTooltips.Name: DID/DNIS
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the direct number dialed by the outside party on an inbound call.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Party Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The type of this party (e.g. Huntgroup, Workgroup, Auto-Attendant).  Station means a user's phone.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Connect Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The reason this party was involved in a call (e.g. they placed the call: 'Originate', they received a call: 'Called', a call was transferred to them: 'Transfer', etc).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Extension
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the ShoreTel extension being reported.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: While you can report on extension, people often find it easier to report on Party Name instead. Both are available for your convenience.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Party Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the name assigned to the extension that you are reporting on.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: The Party name is usually more meaningful to report on the the Extension, but both are available for your convenience.

DimensionTooltips.Name: User Group
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The user group this party is a member of, if any.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Next Party Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The type of destination this call went to next (e.g. another user, voicemail, a hunt group, etc).
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: This is most useful for seeing where hunt group calls are going: whether they are being answered by a user, being abandoned, or being transferred to an overflow destination such as another hunt group or auto-attendant.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Next Party Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Why the call went to the next party (e.g. if it was transferred, the maximum number of rings was reached, etc).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Next Party Extension
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The extension where the call went next, if any.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Next Party Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the party where the call went next, if any.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Answered
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call was answered (had talk time) or only rang and was not answered.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Prev Party Extension
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The extension the call was at previously, if any.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Prev Party Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the party where the call was previously, if any.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Prev Party Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The type of the endpoint this call was at previously (e.g. a hunt group, an auto-attendant, another user, etc).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Disconnect Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The disconnect reason for the current party

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show calls grouped by hour of the day. If you want calls grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Weekday
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the day of the week (Sunday - Saturday)
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the calls for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. calls for Wednesday in week 1 and calls for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together for a total number of calls on Wednesdays.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the calls for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. calls for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of calls under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group calls by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by month of the year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by week

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year-Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The year and month together as a single value
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: Good for grouping data by month in sequential order

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the phone number of the party that placed the call. Note that for an outbound or ext-to-ext call, this field is populated with the extension of the internal party that placed the call.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Dialed Number
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field is the dialed number, regardless of type of call. For an inbound call, this is the same as the DID/DNIS field. For an Outbound call, this is the number dialed by the ShoreTel user, and for Ext-to-Ext calls this is the extension to which the call was placed.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Workgroup Call
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether or not this is a workgroup call.  ShoreTel defines a workgroup call as any call that was handled by a workgroup during its lifetime.  This particular party on the call may or may not have answered the call in the capacity of a workgroup agent.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Trunk
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For inbound and outbound calls, the first trunk that was involved in the call.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID Name
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name, if any, associated with the caller ID.
DetailDimensionTooltips.UseTip: For ExtToExt and Outbound calls this will be the same as the party name, but for Inbound or Tandem calls it will be the name provided with the trunk call, if the service on the trunk supports passing the CallerID name

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Call GUID
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The unique call id (GUID) which can be used to correlate parts of the same call together or with other ShoreTel log information.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Trunk Group
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For inbound and outbound calls, the first trunk group that was involved in the call.

FactTooltips.Name: Count - All Calls
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represents the number of calls being reported and is only available on a summary report.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Call - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: This represent the length of the party's time on the calls being reported (Talk Time + Hold Time).
FactTooltips.UseTip: In a summary report this represents the total duration of all calls reported. In a detail report, this represents the length of each individual call being reported.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Ring - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The time spent ringing of the calls being reported

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Talk - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The talk time of the calls being reported (as opposed to time spent on hold).

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Hold - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The time spent on hold of the calls being reported.

FactTooltips.Name: Overall Call Duration
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total length of the call (in minutes), of which this party might only be one part.
FactTooltips.UseTip: This primarily exists so that the total time of an abandoned call can be reported, in the case when it forwards through multiple destinations.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Next Party - Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The time spent at the next party, if any.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Call - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Average Call Time is a measure of total call duration for this party (ring + talk + hold) divided by the number of calls (both answered and unanswered).  It is only available on summary reports

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Ring - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Average seconds calls ring at this destination

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Talk - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Average talk time per call

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Hold - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Average time calls spend on hold at this destination

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Abandoned
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Abandoned calls are calls in which the caller hung up while waiting for the call to be answered.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: This is the abandon rate as a percentage. This is defined as Abandoned Calls / Total Calls for the given time period

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Abandon - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average amount of time before a call is abandoned.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is only the amount of time that the call rang at this destination, not the total call length (see 'Avg Abandon Call Length')

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Overall Abandoned Call Length Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of calls that are abandoned.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is based on the total length of abandoned calls.  If the call rang at multiple destinations before ending up here and being abandoned, this will represent the total amount of time the caller spent waiting.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Handled by User
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls handled by a user.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: If you are looking at huntgroups, workgroups, or any other such system endpoint, this is the count of calls for which the next destination was a user.  If you are looking at users, this is the count of calls that the user handled and was not forwarded to the no answer or busy destination, redirected to voicemail, or abandoned by the caller.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Forward on Busy
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls forwarded to the busy destination.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is useful to see if a user or hunt group is receiving more calls than they can handle, or if they could handle more calls but their call stack size is configured too low.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - HG/WG Overflow
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls that proceeded to a hunt group or workgroup.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is primarily intended for use on hunt group reports, to see how many calls are overflowing to an overflow hunt group on no answer or busy.  However, if you have a call flow where calls to users might overflow to a hunt group on no answer or busy, such as a receptionist perhaps, this could be useful in that context also.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Handled by Others
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls that were not handled by voicemail, a user, or another hunt group.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is primarily intended for use on hunt group reports, to see how many calls were handled by something other than a user or another hunt group or abandoned by the caller.  However it can be useful in reports around receptionists or other individual users when the next destination type is important.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Count - Handled by VM
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls that proceeded to voicemail
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is useful to see how many of a user's calls are going to voicemail.  It doesn't really work for hunt groups because hunt group's can't forward to voicemail directly.  They can only forward to another endpoint, such as a workgroup, autoattendant, or user that can forward to voicemail, so it will always show as a transfer to that intermediate party and not as a transfer to voicemail.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Next Party - Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Average time the call spent with the next party, if any.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is useful for hunt group reports and similar to see how long the people who answer calls out of the hunt group are spending on those calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Handled by User
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of calls handled by a user.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: If you are looking at huntgroups, workgroups, or any other such system endpoint, this is the count of calls for which the next destination was a user.  If you are looking at users, this is the count of calls that the user handled and was not forwarded to the no answer or busy destination, redirected to voicemail, or abandoned by the caller.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Forward on Busy
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of calls forwarded to the busy destination.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is useful to see if a user or hunt group is receiving more calls than they can handle, or if they could handle more calls but their call stack size is configured too low.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - HG/WG Overflow
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of calls that proceeded to a hunt group or workgroup.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is primarily intended for use on hunt group reports, to see how many calls are overflowing to an overflow hunt group on no answer or busy.  However, if you have a call flow where calls to users might overflow to a hunt group on no answer or busy, such as a receptionist perhaps, this could be useful in that context also.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Handled by Others
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of calls that were not handled by voicemail, a user, or another hunt group.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is primarily intended for use on hunt group reports, to see how many calls were handled by something other than a user or another hunt group or abandoned by the caller.  However it can be useful in reports around receptionists or other individual users when the next destination type is important.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Handled by VM
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of calls that proceeded to voicemail
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: This is useful to see how many of a user's calls are going to voicemail.  It doesn't really work for hunt groups because hunt group's can't forward to voicemail directly.  They can only forward to another endpoint, such as a workgroup, autoattendant, or user that can forward to voicemail, so it will always show as a transfer to that intermediate party and not as a transfer to voicemail.

DetailFactTooltips.Name: Party Count
DetailFactTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of parties involved in this call.
DetailFactTooltips.UseTip: Especially useful for abandoned calls to see how many steps the caller went through before they abandoned the call.

DataSourceTooltip.Name: Call Party Activity
DataSourceTooltip.Tooltip: This data source represents all call activity by each party in the ShoreTel system, including users (stations), hunt groups, route points, workgroups, and others.
DataSourceTooltip.UseTip: Use this data source if you want reports around an individual's (or a system component's) call activity.  Note that unlike 'Call Data', calls can be represented more than once if multiple parties were involved.  For example, if a call comes in to a receptionist, talks to the caller, then transfers the call to person B, the receptionist will be reported as having received a call, and person B will also be reported as having received a call.  It is an accurate indicator of each user's activity, but if you add up the total calls it will be higher than the actual number of calls in the system.  Therefore it should only be used as an indicator of an individual's call activity and not as an indicator of total calls handled by the PBX during a given time period.
