CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Treatment Total
CalculatedFields.Expression: Fact3 + Fact4 + Fact5

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Treatment Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact3 + Fact4 + Fact5 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Queued Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact1) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim6.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{6:Queued}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Ring Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact2) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Talk Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact3 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Hold Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact4 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Wrap Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact5 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered within TASA
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted='{{5:Within TASA}}' THEN Fact0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered without being Queued
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted='{{2:AgentAnswered}}' AND dim6.ValueEncrypted='{{6:Not Queued}}' THEN Fact0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Abandoned
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Abandoned after TASA
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted='{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim5.ValueEncrypted='{{5:After TASA}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Overflowed and Answered
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted='{{2:OtherAnswered}}' THEN Fact16 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Queued
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim6.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{6:Queued}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Interflowed
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:Interflow}}', '{{2:PBXTransfer}}', '{{ReEntered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered in 1st STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:1st}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered in 2nd STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:2nd}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered in 3rd STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:3rd}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered in 4th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:4th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered in 5th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:5th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered in 6th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:6th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 1st STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:1st}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 2nd STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:2nd}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 3rd STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:3rd}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 4th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:4th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 5th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:5th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 6th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:6th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Avg in Queue
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact1) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN Dimension2 IS NULL THEN 900 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: TSF of the group
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' AND dim5.ValueEncrypted = '{{5:Within TASA}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN (dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' AND dim5.ValueEncrypted = '{{5:Within TASA}}') OR (dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}', '{{2:Abandoned}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted = '{{5:After TASA}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Agent RPH
CalculatedFields.Expression: 60 * SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact6), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg Group RPH
CalculatedFields.Expression: 60 * SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN Dimension2 IS NULL THEN 15 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg number of logged-in agents
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact6) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN Dimension2 IS NULL THEN 15 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Release Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact9) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact6) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN Dimension2 IS NULL THEN 15 ELSE 0 END), 0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Wait Total
CalculatedFields.Expression: Fact1 + Fact2

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Wait Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact1 + Fact2) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Agent Transferred
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(Fact13) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered within TASA
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted='{{5:Within TASA}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered without being Queued
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted='{{2:AgentAnswered}}' AND dim6.ValueEncrypted='{{6:Not Queued}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned after TASA
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted='{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim5.ValueEncrypted='{{5:After TASA}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted='{{2:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Queued
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE dim6.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{6:Queued}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 1st STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:1st}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 2nd STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:2nd}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 3rd STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:3rd}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 4th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:4th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 5th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:5th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 6th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:6th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 1st STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:1st}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:1st}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 2nd STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:2nd}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:2nd}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 3rd STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:3rd}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:3rd}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 4th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:4th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:4th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 5th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:5th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:5th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 6th STI
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:6th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:6th}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - No Wrap Code
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim7.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{7:}}', '{{7:No Wrap Code}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls without Wrap Code
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') AND dim7.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{7:}}', '{{7:No Wrap Code}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg number of released agents
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact9) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN Dimension2 IS NULL THEN 15 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Avg number of staffed agents
CalculatedFields.Expression: (SUM(Fact6) - SUM(Fact9)) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN Dimension2 IS NULL THEN 15 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Time at least one agent available
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact8) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN Dimension2 IS NULL THEN 15 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Release %Pct
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact9) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact6), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Max Wait to Abandon
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact14 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Avg Wait to Abandon
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact1 + Fact2 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Overflowed
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact16) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Callback Requested
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:CallbackRequested}}' THEN Fact0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Avg Wait to Answer
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact1 + Fact2 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Agent Call Total
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact3 + Fact4 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Agent Call Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact3 + Fact4 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Accepted
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{11:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{11:InboundACDExternal}}') THEN Fact0 END

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 1 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102) + ' - ' + convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 7 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Call Date_Grp - Interval
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: concat(right(concat('0', datepart(hour, dimension0)), 2), ':', right(concat('0', datepart(minute, dimension0)), 2))

CustomDetailDimensions.Name: Skills
CustomDetailDimensions.PossibleValues: query:SELECT id, name FROM user_fields WHERE type = 's' AND deleted = 'n' and configured = 'y'

CustomDetailDimensions.Name: Call Profiles
CustomDetailDimensions.PossibleValues: query:SELECT id, name FROM user_fields WHERE type = 'u' AND deleted = 'n' and configured = 'y'

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The time and date calls entered the group

DimensionTooltips.Name: Group Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the ECC group.  Agent Queues, which are essentially an optimization of one-agent groups, are identified with an 'AQ' prefix

DimensionTooltips.Name: Exit Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip:
The reason the call left the group.  Typical reasons are:
  AgentAnswered: An agent in the group answered
  OtherAnswered: An agent in an overflow group answered
  Abandoned: The caller hung up while waiting in queue or while ringing at an agent's extensions
  Interflow: The call was interflowed to another destination
  Disconnect: The call ended while in queue, but was not abandoned or interflowed (e.g. the caller requested a callback, or the call was a transfer into this group from another agent and the agent hung up to complete the transfer)

DimensionTooltips.Name: Party Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The next party after the group.  Typically this will be the agent answering the call, if it was answered, or 'None' if the call was abandoned.  In the case of an interflow the destination may not be known, if the interflow destination is outside of ECC (e.g. a ShoreTel voicemail box).

DimensionTooltips.Name: STI
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The Service Time Interval (STI) in which the call exitted the queue (was answered, abandoned, etc).  Service Time Intervals are configured per-group in the Contact Center Director.  The defaults are 10 second intervals up to 50 seconds, with the 6th STI representing 50 seconds and above.  For example, STI 1 represents calls answered or abandoned within 0-10 seconds, STI 2 within 10-20 seconds, and so forth.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Within TASA
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Calls exiting the queue (being answered, abandoned, etc) within the configured Target Average Speed of Answer (TASA).  TASA is configured per group in Contact Center Director and defaults to 20 seconds.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: Filter or break out the data on exit reason to see calls answered within or after TASA, and/or calls abandoned within or after TASA.  If you have a high rate of abandonment before TASA, then your target might be too high relative to how long callers are willing to wait.  If you have a high percentage of calls answered after TASA, then you may need more agents servicing the group to lower wait times.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Queued
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether or not the call was queued.  If agents are available when a call is presented to the group, it will ring straight through to the first available agent without being queued.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you have a high percentage of calls that are not queued, you may have idle capacity in this group.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Wrap Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The wrap code the agent assigned to this call.  Typically wrap codes are used as reason codes for the call, so you can use this to determine the nature of calls being handled by this group, or how much time agents are spending in different reasons for wrap time

DimensionTooltips.Name: DNIS
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The dialed number (DNIS) through which the call entered ECC.  This will not be the external DNIS (i.e. the number the caller called), but rather the IRN configured in ECC to which that number might be mapped.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you have IRNs corresponding to customers, regions, business service areas, or similar, you may use this instead of group to determine the nature of incoming calls, particularly if multiple IRNs are routed to the same agent groups

DimensionTooltips.Name: Answered Group
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The group in which the call was answered, if it was answered.  In the event of an overflow this may be different from the group in which the call was originally queued (i.e. when the exit reason is 'OtherAnswered'.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Target Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The type of the next party after the group.  Normally this should be an ECC agent, but in the case of an abandoned call it will be blank, and if the call was redirected out of ECC it may be a PBX call party (e.g. VM Auto-attendant, etc).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The type of call (should be one of InboundACDInternal, InboundACDExternal, OutboundACD, OutboundAbandonedCallback, or OutboundScheduledCallback).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Service Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the ECC service.

DimensionTooltips.Name: DNIS Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The DNIS name of the IRN that routed the call to the group.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Connect Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The reason the call was presented to the group.  Possible values are 'GroupCall', meaning this was a call directed to the group from a service; 'Overflow', meaning the call was overflowed to the group based on service overflow rules; 'Callback', meaning the call was an outbound scheduled or abandoned callback, which start directly in a group; 'Interflow', which will only apply to an agent queue since a group can not be an interflow target directly.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Short Call
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call was under the 'Short Call Threshold' configured in ECC.  The default is 5 seconds, but it is configurable in Contact Center Director.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Media Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The media type of the contact.  Either Voice, Chat, or Email.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Internal/External
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call was Internal or External. External calls are placed outside of the ShoreTel system, while internal calls are placed to another phone on the same ShoreTel system.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show calls grouped by hour of the day. If you want calls grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Weekday
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the day of the week (Sunday - Saturday)
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the calls for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. calls for Wednesday in week 1 and calls for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together for a total number of calls on Wednesdays.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the calls for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. calls for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of calls under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group calls by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by month of the year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by week

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Interval
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by 15-minute time interval.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Half Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by 30-minute time interval.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The CallerID of the caller, if available.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Customer Name
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the customer.  This will only be populated for outbound dial lists, or inbound calls that are matched by CallerID to a customer using an external database (e.g. a CRM).  You must enable the customer name call profile field in the CCIR configuration area of Contact Center Director.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Transfer Destination
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: If an agent took the call and transferred it, this will be the destination to which they transferred the call.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Customer Number
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The customer number ID.  This will only be populated for outbound dial lists, or inbound calls that are matched by CallerID to a customer using an external database (e.g. a CRM).  You must enable the customer number call profile field in the CCIR configuration area of Contact Center Director.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Email Subject
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For email contacts, the subject of the email

CustomDetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Skills
CustomDetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: User Fields designated by the type 'Skill'

CustomDetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Profiles
CustomDetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: User Fields designated by the type 'Call Profile'

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - All
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total count of calls matching the filters selected.  Use this if you are breaking call counts out by group, agent, disposition, date, etc.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Queued Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time all calls spent in queue for this group.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Ring Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time calls in this group spent ringing at agents

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Talk Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of talk time agents spent on calls in this group.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Hold Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time callers spent on hold with agents in this group.  Note that this is time the caller was put on hold, not time they spent holding in queue before being answered.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Wrap Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time agents spent in wrap mode for calls in this group.
FactTooltips.UseTip: You can break the report out by wrap code to see which wrap codes take the most time.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Login Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total login time to this group for all agents.  For example, if there are three agents logged in to a group for one hour, there would be 180 minutes of login time for that hour.
FactTooltips.UseTip: This is mainly useful to calculate the average number of agents logged in or the percentage of time spent in various modes (wrap, release, etc).  This value will be blank if you filter by Party Name.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - No Agents Available
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time no agents were available, which is when all potentially available agents are utilized and incoming calls would be immediately queued.
FactTooltips.UseTip: Mainly used to calculate percent of time that no agents were available.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - At Least One Avail
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time at least one agent was available, which means if a call were to come in to the group it would ring to an agent and not be immediately queued.
FactTooltips.UseTip: Mainly used to calculate percent of time that at least one agent was available.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Release Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time agents spent in release mode for this group.
FactTooltips.UseTip: Mainly used to calculate the percent of time that agents were in release mode.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Max in Queue
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum number of calls in queue at any given time during the interval covered by the report.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Queued Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum time any call spent in queue during the interval covered by the report.

FactTooltips.Name: Target ASA
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The target average-speed-of-answer (TASA) configured.
FactTooltips.UseTip: This can be used to track changes in TASA configuration over time, but it is also used to calculate the TSF (target service factor) of the group.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Agent Transferred
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls answered by an agent and then transferred to a next destination.
FactTooltips.UseTip: Relate to count of answered calls to determine how many calls are being handled in this group vs how many are transferred on to another destination for resolution.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Wait Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum wait time (queue time + ring time) experienced by a caller during the interval covered by the report.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Treatment Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum treatment time (talk + hold + wrap) for any call during the reporting interval.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Overflowed
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that overflowed beyond this group

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Treatment Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Total talk time, hold time, and wrap time for calls in this group

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Treatment Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average treatment time for calls in this group, which includes Talk time, Hold time, and Wrap time for each call.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Queued Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time calls spend in the queue, if they are queued.  This is the total queue time divided by number of calls that were queued.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Ring Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time calls ring at an agent's extension before being answered.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Talk Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of talk time agents spend on calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Hold Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time agents put calls on hold.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Wrap Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time agents spend in wrap mode for calls in this group.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were answered.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered within TASA
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls answered within the configured Target Average Speed of Answer (TASA).

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered without being Queued
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls answered without being queued.  If agents are available when a call enters a group, it will ring directly to the first available agent without being queued.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Abandoned
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls abandoned.  Calls are abandoned if the caller hangs up while waiting in queue or ringing at an agent's extension.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Abandoned after TASA
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls abandoned after the configured Target Average Speed of Answer (TASA).  These represent callers who had to wait longer than your goal of how quickly calls should be answered, and were not willing to wait any longer.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Overflowed and Answered
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that overflowed to another group and were subsequently answered.  This does not necessarily mean they were answered in an overflow group, but their queue time exceeded the configured duration to overflow to additional groups and they were answered in a group other than this one.  If this group is itself an overflow group it could mean the call was answered in an earlier group.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Queued
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were queued.  If agents are available when a call enters a group, it will ring to the first available agent without being queued.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Interflowed
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were interflowed, according to the interflow settings for the service.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered in 1st STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls answered in the first service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 0-10 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered in 2nd STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls answered in the second service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 10-20 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered in 3rd STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls answered in the third service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 20-30 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered in 4th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls answered in the fourth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 30-40 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered in 5th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls answered in the fifth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 40-50 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered in 6th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls answered in the sixth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents more than 50 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 1st STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls abandoned in the first service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 0-10 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 2nd STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls abandoned in the second service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 10-20 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 3rd STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls abandoned in the third service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 20-30 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 4th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls abandoned in the fourth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 30-40 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 5th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls abandoned in the fifth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 40-50 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Abandoned in 6th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls abandoned in the sixth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents more than 50 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Avg in Queue
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average number of calls in queue at any given time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: TSF of the group
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The target service factor (TSF) of the group.  This is the percentage of calls answered within TASA vs all calls answered and calls abandoned after TASA.  Formally: SUM(Calls answered within TASA) / (SUM(Calls Answered) + SUM(Calls abandoned after TASA)).  Calls answered within TASA only counts calls answered *in this group*, whereas the total number of calls answered includes calls answered after TASA *by any group*.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Agent RPH
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Average requests per hour (RPH), aka calls answered per hour, by agents in this group.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg Group RPH
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Average requests per hour (RPH), aka calls answered per hour, by this group in total.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg number of logged-in agents
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average number of agents logged in to this group at any time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Release Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average amount of time agents spend in release mode of the time they are logged in.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Wait Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total wait time, which is ring time plus queue time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Wait Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average wait time, which is ring time plus queue time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Agent Transferred
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of calls answered by agents that were then transferred to another destination.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of calls that were answered, out of all calls presented to the group.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered within TASA
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of answered calls that were answered within TASA

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered without being Queued
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of answered calls answered without being queued.  If agents are available when a call enters a group, it will ring directly to the first available agent without being queued.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of calls abandoned.  Calls are abandoned if the caller hangs up while waiting in queue or ringing at an agent's extension.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned after TASA
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of abandoned calls abandoned after the configured Target Average Speed of Answer (TASA).  These represent callers who had to wait longer than your goal of how quickly calls should be answered, and were not willing to wait any longer.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Queued
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of calls that were queued.  If agents are available when a call enters a group, it will ring to the first available agent without being queued.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 1st STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls answered in the first service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 0-10 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 2nd STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls answered in the second service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 10-20 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 3rd STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls answered in the third service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 20-30 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 4th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls answered in the fourth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 30-40 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 5th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls answered in the fifth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 40-50 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Answered in 6th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls answered in the sixth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents more than 50 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 1st STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls abandoned in the first service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 0-10 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 2nd STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls abandoned in the second service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 10-20 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 3rd STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls abandoned in the third service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 20-30 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 4th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls abandoned in the fourth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 30-40 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 5th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls abandoned in the fifth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents 40-50 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned in 6th STI
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls abandoned in the sixth service time interval (STI).  By default it represents more than 50 seconds of wait time, but is configurable in ECC.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - No Wrap Code
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were answerd but not assigned a wrap code.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls without Wrap Code
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls that were answered but not assigned a wrap code.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg number of released agents
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average number of agents that were logged in but in release at any given time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Avg number of staffed agents
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average number of agents that were logged in and not in release at any given time (i.e. the staffing level).  This is equivalent to the average number of logged in agents minus the average number of agents in release.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Time at least one agent available
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of time that at least one agent was available

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Release %Pct
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of time that agents were in release in this group.  Note that as this is an overall group metric it will not be broken out by agent.  For per-agent login/release metrics refer to the Agent Data reports.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Max Wait to Abandon
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum wait time (queue + ring) of any abandoned call during the reporting period.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Avg Wait to Abandon
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average wait time (queue + ring) of all abandoned calls during the reporting period.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Overflowed
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls that were overflowed beyond this group.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Callback Requested
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that ended because a callback was requested

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Avg Wait to Answer
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average wait time (queue + ring) of all answered calls during the reporting period (aka 'ASA': Average Speed of Answer).

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Agent Call Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total agent call time for calls in this group.  Equivalent to total talk time plus total hold time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Agent Call Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average agent call time for calls in this group, which includes Talk time and Hold time for each call.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Accepted
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of inbound ACD calls accepted by the group.  This is the total of calls of type InboundACDInternal and InboundACDExternal.

Dimensions.Name: Call Date/Time
Dimensions.SourceColumn: cp.start_time

Dimensions.Name: Agent Name
Dimensions.Proxies: [{"label":"Agent Name"},{"label":"Group Membership","dataSourceType":1310722,"selectionsQuery":"select g_name from ecc.grp","valuesQuery":"select a_name from ecc.grp_agent join ecc.agent using (agent_id) join ecc.grp using (group_id) where g_name in ({{filterValues}})"}]

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Ring Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact1) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Talk Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact2) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Hold Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact3) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact8), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Wrap Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact4) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - ACD presented
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - ACD presented not answered
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{5:PresentedNotAnswered}}', '{{5:Abandoned}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - ACD Answered
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted NOT IN ('{{5:Abandoned}}', '{{5:PresentedNotAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Ring Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}') THEN Fact1 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Talk Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact2 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted NOT IN ('{{5:PresentedNotAnswered}}', '{{5:Abandoned}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Hold Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact3 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact8 ELSE NULL END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Wrap Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact4 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - ACD Held
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact8 ELSE 0 END)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - NACD Incoming
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundNACD}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - NACD Outgoing
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:OutboundNACD}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - NACD Incoming Talk Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundNACD}}') THEN Fact2 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundNACD}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - NACD Outgoing Talk Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:OutboundNACD}}') THEN Fact2 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:OutboundNACD}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: RPH of the agent
CalculatedFields.Expression: 60 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted NOT IN ('{{5:PresentedNotAnswered}}', '{{5:Abandoned}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact12) - ISNULL(SUM(Fact13), 0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Staffed %Pct
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * (SUM(Fact12) - ISNULL(SUM(Fact13), 0)) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact12), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Idle %Pct
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact14) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact12), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - ACD Calls Answered
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted NOT IN ('{{5:PresentedNotAnswered}}', '{{5:Abandoned}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Release Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact13) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact19), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Release %Pct (overall)
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact13) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact12), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Release %Pct (per-group)
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact6) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact5), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Talk %Pct (per-group)
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact2) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact5), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Talk %Pct (overall)
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact2) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact12), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Wrap %Pct (per-group)
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact4) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact5), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Wrap %Pct (overall)
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact4) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact12), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls without wrap code
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim6.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{6:}}', '{{6:No Wrap Code}}') AND dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted NOT IN ('{{5:PresentedNotAnswered}}', '{{5:Abandoned}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted NOT IN ('{{5:PresentedNotAnswered}}', '{{5:Abandoned}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Treatment Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact2 + Fact3 + Fact4) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - No Wrap Code
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim6.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{6:}}', '{{6:No Wrap Code}}') AND dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted NOT IN ('{{5:PresentedNotAnswered}}', '{{5:Abandoned}}') THEN Fact0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Treatment Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact2 + Fact3 + Fact4  ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted NOT IN ('{{5:PresentedNotAnswered}}', '{{5:Abandoned}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE NULL END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Treatment Max
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact16 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Ring Max
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact9 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Talk Max
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact10 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Hold Max
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact15 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - ACD Agent Transferred
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') AND dim5.ValueEncrypted != '{{5:PresentedNotAnswered}}' THEN Fact18 END

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - ACD Agent Transferred

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Talk Total

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Hold Total

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Wrap Total

CalculatedFields.Name: Time ACD - Call Total
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{3:InboundACDInternal}}', '{{3:InboundACDExternal}}', '{{3:InternalACDConsult}}', '{{3:OutboundScheduledCallback}}', '{{3:OutboundAbandonedCallback}}') THEN Fact2 + Fact3 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedDimensions.Expression: convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 1 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102) + ' - ' + convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 7 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102)
