DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The date and time the call reached the agent.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Agent Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the agent.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Group Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the group in which the agent's activity occurred.  This could be blank or a special identifier for non-group-specific activity (e.g. non-ACD calls, release time, etc).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The type of the call: a combination of Inbound or Outbound, ACD or non-ACD (NACD), and Internal or External (e.g. InboundACDExternal).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Connect Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The reason the agent became involved in the call: answered, transferred, etc.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Disconnect Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The reason the agent became uninvolved in the call: disconnect (hangup), transferred, no answer, etc.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Wrap Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The wrap code the agent assigned to the call.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this to break out the data by the types of calls agents are handling.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Release Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The release code for release times, only applicable to Release activity entries.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Agent Id
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The numeric identifier for the agent.  Visible in Contact Center Director as Agent Number / Agent Id.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Internal/External
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call was Internal or External. External calls are placed outside of the ShoreTel system, while internal calls are placed to another phone on the same ShoreTel system.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show calls grouped by hour of the day. If you want calls grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Weekday
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the day of the week (Sunday - Saturday)
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the calls for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. calls for Wednesday in week 1 and calls for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together for a total number of calls on Wednesdays.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the calls for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. calls for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of calls under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group calls by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by month of the year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by week

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Answered
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call was answered by the agent or not.  Disconnect reasons of PresentedNotAnswered and Abandoned count as not answered, anything else counts as answered.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The CallerID of the call, if available.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: DNIS
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The DNIS (IRN) through which the call was received.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Customer Name
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the customer.  This will be populated for outbound dial lists, and for incoming calls if integration is configured to an external database, for example a CRM.  The 'Customer Name' call profile field needs to be included in detail logging on the CCIR configuration page in Contact Center Director.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Transfer Destination
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: If an agent took the call and transferred it, this will be the destination to which they transferred the call.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: DNIS Name
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the IRN/DNIS through which the call was received.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Customer Number
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The customer number ID.  This will be populated for outbound dial lists, and for incoming calls if integration is configured to an external database, for example a CRM.  The 'Customer Number' call profile field needs to be included in detail logging on the CCIR configuration page in Contact Center Director.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - All
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total count of calls matching the filters selected.  Use this if you are breaking out call counts by group, agent, call type, etc.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Ring Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of ring time (in seconds) across all corresponding calls.  Mainly used for calculating average ring time per call.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Talk Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of talk time (in minutes) across all corresponding calls.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Hold Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of hold time (in minutes) across all corresponding calls.  Hold time is when an agent puts a call on hold -- it is not queue time, when a caller is waiting for an agent to become available.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Wrap Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of wrap time across all corresponding calls.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Login (per group)
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time (in minutes) the agent was logged in to a particular group.  Note that if an agent is logged in to multiple groups for overlapping time ranges, the sum of login times will exceed the overall login time.  Therefore this field is only useful on reports broken out by group or filtered to a specific group.  For overall login time irrespective of group, please refer to the 'Time - Login (overall)' value.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Release (per group)
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time (in minutes) the agent spent in release mode.  Note that if an agent is logged in to multiple groups, they will be in release mode in all groups for the same time and the sum of release times will exceed the overall release time.  Therefore this field is only useful on reports broken out by group or filtered to a specific group.  For overall release time, please refer to the 'Time - Release (overall)' value.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Idle (per group)
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time the agent was idle (available for a call -- not in release, wrap, or on another call).  Note that if an agent is logged in to multiple groups they will be idle in all groups for the same time, and the sum of the idle times will exceed the overall idle time. Therefore this field is only useful on reports broken out by group or filtered to a specific group.  For overall idle time, please refer to the 'Time - Idle (overall)' value.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Held
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of calls the agent put on hold.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Ring Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The longest ring time (in seconds) observed during the reporting period.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Talk Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The longest talk time (in minutes) observed during the reporting period.

FactTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Wrap Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The longest warp time (in minutes) observed during the reporting period.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Login (overall)
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The overall amount of time the agent was logged in to any group.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Release (overall)
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The overall amount of time the agent was in release mode for any group.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Idle (overall)
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The overall amount of time the agent was idle in any group.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Hold Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum amount of time the agent put a call on hold during the reporting period.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Treatment Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum treatment time (talk + hold + wrap, in minutes) during the reporting period.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Release Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum release time for any single release state during the reporting period.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Agent Transferred
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls the agent transferred on to another destination, rather than ending with the agent. Note: this takes in to account non-ACD calls, which can further include calls that were forwarded by call handling and not necessarily answered by the agent.  For strictly ACD calls that the agent answered and then transferred, please refer to 'Call Count - ACD Agent Transferred'.

FactTooltips.Name: Release Count
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of release events by the agent during the reporting period.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Ring Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time, per call, that calls rang at this agent's extension.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Talk Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time that the agent spent in talk time on each call.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Hold Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time, per call, the agent put the caller on hold.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Wrap Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time, per call, the agent spent in wrap mode.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - ACD presented
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of ACD calls presented to the agent, meaning they rang to the agent's extension because they were available.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - ACD presented not answered
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of ACD calls that were presented to the agent but were not answered.  This could be because the caller hung up while the call was ringing, or because the agent did not answer and the caller went back in queue or to the next available agent.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - ACD Answered
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of ACD calls that the agent answered.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Ring Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time, in seconds per call, that ACD calls rang at the agent's extension before being either answered, abandoned, or requeued for another agent.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Talk Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time, in minutes per call, that the agent spent in talk time on ACD calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Hold Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time, in minutes per call, that ACD calls were put on hold.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Wrap Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time, in minutes per call, that the agent spent in wrap mode on ACD calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - ACD Held
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of ACD calls that the agent put on hold.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - NACD Incoming
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of incoming non-ACD calls to the agent.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - NACD Outgoing
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of outgoing non-ACD calls placed by the agent.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - NACD Incoming Talk Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of talk time, in minutes per call, the agent spent on incoming non-ACD calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - NACD Outgoing Talk Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of talk time, in minutes per call, the agent spent on outgoing non-ACD calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: RPH of the agent
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The requests per hour (aka ACD calls handled per hour) by the agent.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Staffed %Pct
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total time logged in minus the time in release mode (i.e. the time the agent was ready and waiting for or on a call), as a percentage of total logged in time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Idle %Pct
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The idle time as a percentage of the total logged in time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - ACD Calls Answered
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of ACD calls presented to the agent that the agent answered

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Release Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average amount of time spent in release per each release interval.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Release %Pct (overall)
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of overall login time spent in release mode.  Note: this can be broken out by release code, but can not be filtered or broken out by group.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Release %Pct (per-group)
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of per-group login time spent in release mode.  Note: this should be used on reports filtered to a single group or broken out by group.  It can not be broken out or filtered by release code, for that please refer to 'Time - Release %Pct (overall)'.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Talk %Pct (per-group)
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of per-group login time spent in active talk time.  Note: the per-group talk time can be broken out by group in order to see in which group the agent is spending most of their talking time.  The total for the section will be inaccurate however since all login time will be added together for each group, which will be more than their actual login time.  In order to see the percent of login time the agent spent talking in any group you need to use 'Time - Talk %Pct (overall)' instead or in addition.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Talk %Pct (overall)
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of overall login time spent in active talk time.  Note: since the overall login time is irrespective of group, this value can not be broken out or filtered by group.  For that, refer to 'Time - Talk %Pct (per-group) instead.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Wrap %Pct (per-group)
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of per-group login time spent in wrap mode.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Wrap %Pct (overall)
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of overall login time spent in wrap mode.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls without wrap code
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of ACD calls that the agent did not assign a wrap code.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Treatment Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average treatment time (Talk + Hold + Wrap divided by count of all calls)

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - No Wrap Code
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The count of ACD calls that the agent did not assign a wrap code.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Treatment Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time, in minutes per call, that the agent spent in talk plus hold plus wrap time on ACD calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Treatment Max
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The max treatment time (talk + hold + wrap) the agent spent on any ACD call.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Ring Max
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum amount of time the agent let an ACD call ring.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Talk Max
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The max talk time the agent spent on any ACD call.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Hold Max
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum length of time the agent put any ACD call on hold.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - ACD Agent Transferred
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The count of ACD calls the agent answered and transferred to another destination

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - ACD Agent Transferred
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of ACD calls the agent answered and transferred to another destination

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Agent staffing (overall)
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The amount of time the agent was logged in and not in release.  This uses overall login time (login time irrespective of group) and overall release time, so you can filter on release code if you define the time the agent is staffing the call center as including or excluding certain release codes.  However you can not filter by group since overall (non-group-specific) time is used.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Agent staffing (per-group)
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The amount of time the agent was logged in and not in release.  This uses per-group login and release time, so if you filter to a single group or break out the report by group you can see the time the agent was staffing each group.  However you can not include or exclude any specific release codes since that detail is not provided for per-group release time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Call Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The sum of talk time and hold time (i.e. the total length of the call) for all calls.
CalculatedFieldTooltips.UseTip: Break this out by Call Type in the Rows to see specifics around each call type. To see call time for only ACD calls, use Time ACD - Call Total.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Talk Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total talk time for ACD calls only.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Hold Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total hold time for ACD calls only.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Wrap Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total wrap time for ACD calls only.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Call Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total call time (talk + hold) for ACD calls only.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time ACD - Treatment Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total treatment time (talk + hold + wrap) for all ACD calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - NACD Talk Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total length of talk time, in minutes per call, the agent spent on incoming and outgoing non-ACD calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - NACD Incoming Talk Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total length of talk time, in minutes per call, the agent spent on incoming non-ACD calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - NACD Outgoing Talk Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total length of talk time, in minutes per call, the agent spent on outgoing non-ACD calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - NACD Talk Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of talk time, in minutes per call, the agent spent on both incoming and outgoing non-ACD calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Call Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average call time, which is talk time plus hold time

Dimensions.Name: Call Date/Time
Dimensions.SourceColumn: start_time

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Treatment Total
CalculatedFields.Expression: Fact3 + Fact4 + Fact5

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Treatment Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact3 + Fact4 + Fact5) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Queued Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact1) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim4.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{4:Queued}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Ring Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact2) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Talk Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact3) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Hold Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact4) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Wrap Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact5) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Answered without being Queued
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted='{{2:AgentAnswered}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted='{{4:Not Queued}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Abandoned
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Overflowed
CalculatedFields.Expression: Fact9

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Queued
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim4.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{4:Queued}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Call Count - Interflowed
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Interflow}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Wait Total
CalculatedFields.Expression: Fact1 + Fact2

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Wait Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact1 + Fact2) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Agent Transferred
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100.0 * SUM(Fact7) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:AgentAnswered}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Avg Wait To Answer
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact1 + Fact2 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:AgentAnswered}}', '{{2:OtherAnswered}}') THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE dim2.ValueEncrypted WHEN '{{2:Abandoned}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 1 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102) + ' - ' + convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 7 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102)

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The time and date calls entered the group

DimensionTooltips.Name: Service Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the ECC service.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Exit Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip:
The reason the call left the service.  Typical reasons are:
  AgentAnswered: An agent in the primary service group answered
  OtherAnswered: An agent in an overflow group answered
  Abandoned: The caller hung up while waiting in queue or while ringing at an agent's extensions
  Interflow: The call was interflowed to another destination
  Disconnect: The call ended while in queue, but was not abandoned or interflowed and no further context could be determined.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Party Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The next party after the service.  Typically this will be the agent answering the call, if it was answered, or 'None' if the call was abandoned.  In the case of an interflow the destination may not be known, if the interflow destination is outside of ECC (e.g. a ShoreTel voicemail box).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Queued
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether or not the call was queued.  If agents are available when a call is presented to the group, it will ring straight through to the first available agent without being queued.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you have a high percentage of calls that are not queued, you may have idle capacity in this group.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Wrap Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The wrap code the agent assigned to this call.  Typically wrap codes are used as reason codes for the call, so you can use this to determine the nature of calls being handled by this group, or how much time agents are spending in different reasons for wrap time

DimensionTooltips.Name: DNIS
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The dialed number (DNIS) through which the call entered ECC.  This will not be the external DNIS (i.e. the number the caller called), but rather the IRN configured in ECC to which that number might be mapped.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you have IRNs corresponding to customers, regions, business service areas, or similar, you may use this instead of service name to determine the nature of incoming calls, particularly if multiple IRNs are routed to the same service.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Answered Group
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The group in which the call was answered, if it was answered.  In the event of an overflow this may be different from the group in which the call was originally queued (i.e. when the exit reason is 'OtherAnswered'.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Target Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The type of the next party after the group.  Normally this should be an ECC agent, but in the case of an abandoned call it will be blank, and if the call was redirected out of ECC it may be a PBX call party (e.g. VM Auto-attendant, etc).

DimensionTooltips.Name: STI
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The Service Time Interval (STI) in which the call ended (was Answered, Abandoned, etc).  This is the STI for the associated IRN through which the call was routed.  STIs for IRNs are configured independently from STIs for Groups.

DimensionTooltips.Name: TASA
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call ended (was Answered, Abandoned, etc) within TASA or after TASA.  This is the TASA for the associated IRN through which the call was routed.  TASA for IRNs are configured independently from TASA for Groups.  If the call came to the service some way other than through an IRN destination (e.g. an interflow rule or script action), this field will not be populated.

DimensionTooltips.Name: DNIS Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The DNIS name of the IRN that routed the call to the service.  If the call came to the service some way other than through an IRN (e.g. an interflow rule or script action), this field will not be populated.

DimensionTooltips.Name: IRN
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The IRN that routed the call to the service.  If the call came to the service some way other than through an IRN (e.g. an interflow rule or script action), this field will not be populated.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The type of call (InboundACDInternal, InboundACDExternal, ACDEmail, ACDChat)

DimensionTooltips.Name: Internal/External
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the call was Internal or External. External calls are placed outside of the ShoreTel system, while internal calls are placed to another phone on the same ShoreTel system.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Connect Reason
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The reason the call was presented to the service.  Primarily either normal call or interflow from another service.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show calls grouped by hour of the day. If you want calls grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Weekday
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the day of the week (Sunday - Saturday)
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the calls for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. calls for Wednesday in week 1 and calls for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together for a total number of calls on Wednesdays.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the calls for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. calls for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of calls under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group calls by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by month of the year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Year
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Week
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by week

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date_Grp - Half Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by 30-minute time interval.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: CallerID
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The CallerID of the caller, if available.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Customer Name
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the customer.  This will only be populated for outbound dial lists, or inbound calls that are matched by CallerID to a customer using an external database (e.g. a CRM).  You must enable the customer name call profile field in the CCIR configuration area of Contact Center Director.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Customer Number
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The customer number ID.  This will only be populated for outbound dial lists, or inbound calls that are matched by CallerID to a customer using an external database (e.g. a CRM).  You must enable the customer number call profile field in the CCIR configuration area of Contact Center Director.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - All
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total count of calls matching the filters selected.  Use this if you are breaking call counts out by group, agent, disposition, date, etc.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Queued Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time all calls spent in queue for this group.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Ring Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time calls in this group spent ringing at agents

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Talk Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of talk time agents spent on calls in this group.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Hold Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time callers spent on hold with agents in this group.  Note that this is time the caller was put on hold, not time they spent holding in queue before being answered.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Wrap Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total amount of time agents spent in wrap mode for calls in this group.
FactTooltips.UseTip: You can break the report out by wrap code to see which wrap codes take the most time.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Queued Max
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum time any call spent in queue during the interval covered by the report.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Agent Transferred
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls answered by an agent and then transferred to a next destination.
FactTooltips.UseTip: Relate to count of answered calls to determine how many calls are being handled in this group vs how many are transferred on to another destination for resolution.

FactTooltips.Name: Time - Duration Total
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total duration of time spent in the service.  This may be larger than queue time plus ring time if there are pre-group actions such as a mandatory announcement.

FactTooltips.Name: Call Count - Overflowed
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The count of calls that overflowed while in queue

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Treatment Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: Total talk time, hold time, and wrap time for calls in this group

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Treatment Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average treatment time for calls in this group, which includes Talk time, Hold time, and Wrap time for each call.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Queued Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time calls spend in the queue, if they are queued.  This is the total queue time divided by number of calls that were queued.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Ring Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time calls ring at an agent's extension before being answered.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Talk Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of talk time agents spend on calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Hold Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time agents put calls on hold.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Wrap Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average length of time agents spend in wrap mode for calls in this group.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were answered.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Answered without being Queued
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls answered without being queued.  If agents are available when a call enters a group, it will ring directly to the first available agent without being queued.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Abandoned
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls abandoned.  Calls are abandoned if the caller hangs up while waiting in queue or ringing at an agent's extension.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Overflowed
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that overflowed to another group.  This does not necessarily mean they were answered in an overflow group, but their queue time exceeded the configured duration to overflow to additional groups.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Queued
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were queued.  If agents are available when a call enters a group, it will ring to the first available agent without being queued.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Call Count - Interflowed
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were interflowed, according to the interflow settings for the service.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Wait Total
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total wait time, which is ring time plus queue time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Wait Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average wait time, which is ring time plus queue time.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Agent Transferred
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percentage of calls answered by agents that were then transferred to another destination.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Avg Wait To Answer
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average wait time, which is ring time plus queue time, for answered calls

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: %Pct - Calls Abandoned
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The percent of calls abandoned.  Calls are abandoned if the caller hangs up while waiting in queue or ringing at an agent's extension.

CalculatedFields.Expression: return Math.round(100 * data.callsAnswered / data.callsTotal)

FactTooltips.Name: Calls in Queue
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls currently in the workgroup queue

FactTooltips.Name: Max Wait Time
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The longest wait time (in seconds) of calls currently in queue

FactTooltips.Name: Avg Wait Time
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The average wait time (in seconds) that calls currently in queue have been waiting

FactTooltips.Name: Total Calls Today
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of calls handled by the workgroup today

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Presented and Answered
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of calls normally answered by the workgroup today

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Abandoned Today
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of calls abandoned in the workgroup today

FactTooltips.Name: Avg Wait Time Today
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The average wait time of calls through the group today

FactTooltips.Name: Max Wait Time Today
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The maximum wait time of any call through the group today

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Deflected Today
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were not presented to the group, either because no agents were logged in, no agents were available, or off-hours call handling was in effect

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Forward-Always
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls today with an exit reason of ForwardAlways.  Typically these will be off-hours calls.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Forward-Busy
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls today with an exit reason of ForwardBusy.  If all agents are busy and the call handling rule is not 'Queue', a call will have this exit reason.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Forward-No-Agent
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls today with an exit reason of ForwardNoAgent.  If no agents are logged in and the call handling rule is not 'Queue', a call will have this exit reason.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Forward-No-Answer
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls today with an exit reason of ForwardNoAnswer.  If the maximum number of rings is reached and the call handling rule is not 'Queue', a call will have this exit reason.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Interflowed
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls today with an exit reason of Interflowed.  If the call queues until the last queue step and reaches the interflow rule, it will have this exit reason.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Overflowed
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls today with an exit reason of Overflowed.  If the call queues until the last queue step and reaches the overflow rule, it will have this exit reason.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Picked up
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls today with an exit reason of Pickup.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Unparked
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls today with an exit reason if Unpark.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Transferred Out
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were transferred out of the queue due to an action by the caller.  These are calls where the caller pressed a button in order to be transferred to voicemail, an auto-attendant menu, or another destination.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Transferred to Voicemail
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were transferred to voicemail due to a key press by the caller.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Transferred to Menu
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were transferred to a menu due to a key press by the caller.

FactTooltips.Name: Calls Transferred to Extension
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of calls that were transferred to an extension due to a key press by the caller.

FactTooltips.Name: Number of Agents Logged In
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of agents logged in to a given Workgroup.

FactTooltips.Name: Number of Agents Available
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The number of agents available in a given Workgroup.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Percent of Calls Answered
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of answered calls divided by the total number of calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Percent of Calls Abandoned
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of abandoned calls divided by the total number of calls.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Calls Answered Today
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The total number of calls answered today, including normally answered and picked up from the queue using software or IP phone buttons.

CalculatedFields.Name: Active Calls
CalculatedFields.Expression: return Math.round(data.activeInboundCalls + data.activeOutboundCalls)

CalculatedFields.Name: Max Active Call Length
CalculatedFields.Expression: var i=data.maxActiveInboundCallLength, o=data.maxActiveOutboundCallLength; return (i ? i.value : -1) >= (o ? o.value : -1) ? i : o

CalculatedFields.Name: Total Calls
CalculatedFields.Expression: return Math.round(data.totalInboundCalls + data.totalOutboundCalls)

CalculatedFields.Name: Total Usage
CalculatedFields.Expression: return Math.round(data.totalInboundUsage + data.totalOutboundUsage)

CalculatedFields.Name: Percent Trunk Usage
CalculatedFields.Expression: return Math.round((data.activeInboundCalls + data.activeOutboundCalls) / data.totalTrunkCount * 100)

CalculatedFields.Name: Percent Inbound Trunk Usage
CalculatedFields.Expression: return Math.round(data.activeInboundCalls / data.totalTrunkCount * 100)

CalculatedFields.Name: Percent Outbound Trunk Usage
CalculatedFields.Expression: return Math.round(data.activeOutboundCalls / data.totalTrunkCount * 100)

CalculatedFields.Name: Percent Max Trunk Utilization
CalculatedFields.Expression: return Math.round(data.maxCalls / data.totalTrunkCount * 100)

CalculatedFields.Name: Percent Max Inbound Trunk Utilization
CalculatedFields.Expression: return Math.round(data.maxInboundCalls / data.totalTrunkCount * 100)

CalculatedFields.Name: Percent Max Outbound Trunk Utilization
CalculatedFields.Expression: return Math.round(data.maxOutboundCalls / data.totalTrunkCount * 100)

DimensionTooltips.Name: Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Date and time of this session.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Direction
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The direction of the interaction -- (Inbound or Outbound)

DimensionTooltips.Name: DNIS
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The inbound number (or other address, for example email) on which the interaction came in.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Queue Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The queue name associated with this session of the interaction.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: This may not be the first or only queue associated with the interaction.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Media Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The media type of the session. Could be Voice, Chat, Email, Message, Callback, etc.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Participant Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the participant for the session.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: This may show 'External' or 'Customer' for external parties.  For internal parties, it will display the name of the IVR, agent, queue, etc.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Wrap Up Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The wrap up code applied to this session of the interaction.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Skill
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: A unique identifier for the language requested for an interaction.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Disconnect Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The reason this session of the interaction ended. For example, 'Peer' means the other party disconnected, 'Transfer' means the interaction was transferred to another destination, etc.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip:
Client: The PureCloud user interface caused the disconnect. For example, an agent clicked End Call during a voice interaction or discarded an email interaction. 
Conference Transfer: The PureCloud user transferred the conversation to a conference. 
Consult Transfer: The PureCloud user started a consult transfer.
Endpoint: A users endpoint caused the disconnect. For example, the user hung up their physical phone or the browser closed while using the PureCloud WebRTC phone.
Error: An error in the provider caused the disconnect.
Forward Transfer: A transfer to forward the interaction caused the disconnect.
No Answer Transfer: A transfer after an alerting timeout caused the disconnect.
Not Available Transfer: A transfer due to a not available status caused the disconnect.
Other: A segment disconnected for reasons not covered by the other categories. 
Peer:  The other party disconnected
Spam: AWS spam filtering marked an email interaction as spam, and PureCloud disconnected that interaction. 
System: The system ended the session
Timeout: The cloud or the provider caused the disconnect. 
Transfer: A transfer caused the disconnect.
Transport Failure: An ICE failure caused the disconnect.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Conference
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: True/False field indicating if the participant was conferenced in this session.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Language

DimensionTooltips.Name: Purpose
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Identifies the type of participant involved in this session. (e.g. Agent, User, Acd, Customer, Fax, External, etc)

DimensionTooltips.Name: User Id
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The user Id for the participant if that participant was an agent (user).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Internal/External
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Identifies the call as External or Internal.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Work Team Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The 'Work Team Name' for the agent

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show interactions grouped by hour of the day. If you want interactions grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Weekday
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the day of the week (Sunday - Saturday)
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the interactions for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. interactions for Wednesday in week 1 and interactions for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together for a total number of interactions on Wednesdays.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the interactions for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. interactions for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of interactions under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group interactions by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedFields.Expression: COALESCE(Fact1, 0) + COALESCE(Fact2, 0)

CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim8.ValueEncrypted = '{{8:Answered}}' THEN Fact0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Abandoned

DimensionTooltips.Name: Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The date and time at which the interaction entered the queue

The fields 'abandoned in 1st interval', etc, can be used to see the interval applied specifically to abandoned interactions.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Area Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The area code of the caller, if CallerID is available.

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Handle Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact1) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim14.ValueEncrypted = '{{14:Handled}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Talk Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact3) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim14.ValueEncrypted = '{{14:Handled}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Hold Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact4) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact8), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Wrap Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact5) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim14.ValueEncrypted = '{{14:Handled}}' AND dim4.ValueEncrypted <> '{{4:}}' THEN COALESCE(Fact13, Fact0) ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Transfer
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim14.ValueEncrypted = '{{14:Handled}}' THEN CASE WHEN dim9.ValueEncrypted = '{{9:Transfer}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END END)

CalculatedFields.Name: %PCT - Transfer
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim14.ValueEncrypted = '{{14:Handled}}' THEN CASE WHEN dim9.ValueEncrypted = '{{9:Transfer}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim14.ValueEncrypted = '{{14:Handled}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Talk - ACD
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim1.ValueEncrypted = '{{1:ACD}}' THEN Fact3 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Talk - NACD
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim1.ValueEncrypted = '{{1:non-ACD}}' THEN Fact3 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - ACD Conversations
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim1.ValueEncrypted = '{{1:ACD}}' AND dim14.ValueEncrypted = '{{14:Handled}}' THEN Fact0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Login Total
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{11:Offline}}') THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Not Responding
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim13.ValueEncrypted = '{{13:NotResponding}}' THEN Fact7 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - On Queue
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:On Queue}}' THEN Fact6 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Idle
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim13.ValueEncrypted = '{{13:Idle}}' THEN Fact7 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Meal
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Meal}}' THEN Fact6 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Training
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Training}}' THEN Fact6 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - In Meetings
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Meeting}}' THEN Fact6 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Busy
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Busy}}' THEN Fact6 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - On Break
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Break}}' THEN Fact6 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Available
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Available}}' THEN Fact6 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Away
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Away}}' THEN Fact6 END

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - Not Responding
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim13.ValueEncrypted = '{{13:NotResponding}}' THEN Fact7 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim13.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{13:Interacting}}', '{{13:Idle}}', '{{13:NotResponding}}') THEN Fact7 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - On Queue
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:On Queue}}' THEN Fact6 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Offline}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - Idle
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim13.ValueEncrypted = '{{13:Idle}}' THEN Fact7 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim13.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{13:Interacting}}', '{{13:Idle}}', '{{13:NotResponding}}') THEN Fact7 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - Meal
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Meal}}' THEN Fact6 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Offline}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - Training
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Training}}' THEN Fact6 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Offline}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - In Meetings
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Meeting}}' THEN Fact6 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Offline}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - Busy
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Busy}}' THEN Fact6 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Offline}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - On Break
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Break}}' THEN Fact6 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Offline}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - Available
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Available}}' THEN Fact6 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Offline}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - Away
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Away}}' THEN Fact6 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Offline}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Interacting
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim13.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{13:Interacting}}') THEN Fact7 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - Interacting
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim13.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{13:Interacting}}') THEN Fact7 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim13.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{13:Interacting}}', '{{13:Idle}}', '{{13:NotResponding}}') THEN Fact7 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Total ACD
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim13.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{13:Interacting}}', '{{13:Idle}}', '{{13:NotResponding}}') THEN Fact7 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Off Queue
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{11:On Queue}}', '{{11:Offline}}') THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - Off Queue
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{11:On Queue}}', '{{11:Offline}}') THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:Offline}}' THEN 0 ELSE Fact6 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Total Outbound
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Outbound}}' THEN Fact3 ELSE 0 END)

CalculatedFields.Name: %PCT - Handled
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(CASE WHEN dim14.ValueEncrypted = '{{14:Handled}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Alerting Avg
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(Fact2) / NULLIF(SUM(Fact0), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: %Time - Wrap
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * SUM(Fact5) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted = '{{11:On Queue}}' THEN Fact6 END), 0)

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Handled
CalculatedFields.Expression: CASE WHEN dim14.ValueEncrypted = '{{14:Handled}}' THEN Fact0 ELSE 0 END

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Days Worked
CalculatedFields.Expression: COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN dim11.ValueEncrypted NOT IN ('{{11:}}', '{{11:Offline}}') THEN CAST(Dimension0 AS Date) END)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Date Group - Week
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 1 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102) + ' - ' + convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 7 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Date Group - 15 min
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: concat(right(concat('0', datepart(hour, Dimension0)), 2), ':', right(concat('0', datepart(minute, Dimension0)), 2))

DimensionTooltips.Name: Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The date and time at which the interaction or status change occurred

DimensionTooltips.Name: Category
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The category of agent activity, could be Presence, Routing Status, ACD, or non-ACD activity

DimensionTooltips.Name: Direction
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The direction of the interaction -- Inbound, Outbound, or Callback (which comprises both an inbound and outbound portion).

DimensionTooltips.Name: DNIS
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The inbound number (or other address, for example email) on which the interaction came in.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Queue Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The queue through which the interaction was received (only applies to ACD activity)

DimensionTooltips.Name: Media Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The media type of the interaction.  Could be Voice, Chat, Email, Message, etc.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Agent Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the agent (user).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Wrap Up Code
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For ACD interactions, the wrap code that was applied.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Skill
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Any skill that was requested for an interaction.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Disconnect Type
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The reason the interaction ended.  For example, 'Peer' means the other party disconnected, 'Transfer' means the interaction was transferred to another destination, etc.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip:
Client: The PureCloud user interface caused the disconnect. For example, an agent clicked End Call during a voice interaction or discarded an email interaction. 
Conference Transfer: The PureCloud user transferred the conversation to a conference. 
Consult Transfer: The PureCloud user started a consult transfer.
Endpoint: A user's endpoint caused the disconnect. For example, the user hung up their physical phone or the browser closed while using the PureCloud WebRTC phone.
Error: An error in the provider caused the disconnect.
Forward Transfer: A transfer to forward the interaction caused the disconnect.
No Answer Transfer: A transfer after an alerting timeout caused the disconnect.
Not Available Transfer: A transfer due to a not available status caused the disconnect.
Other: A segment disconnected for reasons not covered by the other categories. 
Peer:  The other party disconnected
Spam: AWS spam filtering marked an email interaction as spam, and PureCloud disconnected that interaction. 
System: The system ended the session
Timeout: The cloud or the provider caused the disconnect. 
Transfer: A transfer caused the disconnect.
Transport Failure: An ICE failure caused the disconnect.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Language
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Any language that was requested for an interaction.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Primary Status
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For user presence time tracking, this is the system-defined type of presence status the user is in.  For example, Meeting, Break, Available, On-Queue.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Secondary Status
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For user presence time tracking, this is the organizational name of the presence status, aka Secondary Status.

DimensionTooltips.Name: ACD Status
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For routing status time tracking, the type of ACD routing status the agent is in.  In general, routing status is 'Off-Queue' unless the agent's primary status (aka 'presence') is 'On-Queue'.  While the agent is On-Queue, they may have a status of 'Idle', 'Interacting', 'Not responding', etc.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Outcome
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Whether the interaction was answered ('Handled'), rang the max number of rings and was not answered ('Not Responding'), 'Abandoned' while the interaction was ringing, or not answered by the agent ('Not Handled').

DimensionTooltips.Name: User Id
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The user Id of the agent (user).

DimensionTooltips.Name: Internal/External
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Identifies the call as External or Internal.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Work Team Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The 'Work Team Name' for the agent

DimensionTooltips.Name: Agent Division
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the Division the agent (user) belongs to.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show interactions grouped by hour of the day. If you want interactions grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Weekday
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the day of the week (Sunday - Saturday)
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the interactions for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. interactions for Wednesday in week 1 and interactions for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together for a total number of interactions on Wednesdays.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the interactions for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. interactions for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of interactions under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group interactions by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by month of the year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Year
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by year

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Week
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by week

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - 15 min
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by 15-minute time interval.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - 30 min
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Groups data by 30-minute time interval.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The unique identifier for the conversation.  Can be used to correlate interactions with other PureCloud data, or the same interactions across multiple agents/queues.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Subject
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: For email interactions, the subject of the email.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: Wrap Up Note
DetailDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Any wrap-up note the agent may have added.

DetailDimensionTooltips.Name: ANI

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Handle Avg

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Talk Avg
CalculatedFieldTooltips.Tooltip: The average talk/interaction time for each interaction that was handled.

CalculatedFieldTooltips.Name: Time - Hold Avg

CalculatedFields.Name: %PCT - Adherence
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * (1 - (ISNULL(SUM(Fact2), 0) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted IN ('{{2:Adherence}}', '{{2:Exception}}') THEN Fact1 ELSE 0 END), 0)))

CalculatedFields.Name: %PCT - Conformance
CalculatedFields.Expression: 100 * (SUM(CASE WHEN dim5.ValueEncrypted = '{{5:OnQueue}}' THEN Fact1 ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted = '{{3:Onqueuework}}' THEN Fact1 ELSE 0 END), 0))

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Total Adhering
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim2.ValueEncrypted = '{{2:Adherence}}' THEN Fact1 ELSE 0 END)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Total Scheduled
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted <> '{{3:Unscheduled}}' THEN Fact1 ELSE 0 END)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Total Conforming
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim5.ValueEncrypted = '{{5:OnQueue}}' THEN Fact1 ELSE 0 END)

CalculatedFields.Name: Count - Days Worked
CalculatedFields.Expression: COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN dim5.ValueEncrypted NOT IN ('{{5:Offline}}') THEN CAST(Dimension0 AS Date) END)

CalculatedFields.Name: Time - Total Unpaid
CalculatedFields.Expression: SUM(CASE WHEN dim3.ValueEncrypted <> '{{3:Unscheduled}}' THEN Fact1 ELSE 0 END) - ISNULL(SUM(Fact3), 0)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Date Group - Week
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 1 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102) + ' - ' + convert(nvarchar, dateadd(dd, 7 - datepart(dw, Dimension0), Dimension0), 102)

CalculatedDimensions.Name: Date Group - 15 min
CalculatedDimensions.Expression: concat(right(concat('0', datepart(hour, Dimension0)), 2), ':', right(concat('0', datepart(minute, Dimension0)), 2))

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show interactions grouped by hour of the day. If you want interactions grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Weekday
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the day of the week (Sunday - Saturday)
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the interactions for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. interactions for Wednesday in week 1 and interactions for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together for a total number of interactions on Wednesdays.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the interactions for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. interactions for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of interactions under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group interactions by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Call Date/Time
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: Date and time of this session.

DimensionTooltips.Name: DNIS
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The inbound number (or other address, for example email) on which the call or other interaction came in.

DimensionTooltips.Name: Disposition
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: How the call left the queue (i.e. was answered or abandoned)

DimensionTooltips.Name: Queue Name
DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The queue name associated with this session of the call.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: This may not be the first or only queue associated with the call.

DimensionTooltips.Tooltip: The name of the participant for the session.
DimensionTooltips.UseTip: This may show 'External' or 'Customer' for external parties.  For internal parties, it will display the name of the IVR, agent, queue, etc.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Hour
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the hours of the day.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: You can use this field in two ways. If you want to limit your report to certain hours of the day (8am-5pm for example) you can filter on this field. In addition, you can add this field to your report to show calls grouped by hour of the day. If you want calls grouped by date and hour of the day, consider filtering on this field, but including the Call Date/Time field instead of this one in your report.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Weekday
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the day of the week (Sunday - Saturday)
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you include this field and your time range spans multiple weeks, the calls for the day of the week will be added together. i.e. calls for Wednesday in week 1 and calls for Wednesday in week 2 will be added together for a total number of calls on Wednesdays.

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Day of Month
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This is the number day of the month (01-31).
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If your time range spans multiple months, the calls for the number days of the month will be added together. i.e. calls for June 15 and July 15 will be added together for a total number of calls under the 15 day of the month

CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Name: Date Group - Full Date
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.Tooltip: This field represents the date and day of week and is formated as yyyy-mm-dd weekday.
CalculatedDimensionTooltips.UseTip: If you want to group calls by day, use this field. You cannot filter on this field as it is a calculated field. Filter on the Call Date/Time field to get the date range you want, and include this field to group the report by dates.

CalculatedFields.Name: Average Talk Time - Voice
CalculatedFields.Expression: return data.totalTalkCount && (data.totalTalkTime / data.totalTalkCount)

CalculatedFields.Name: Average Wrap Time - Voice
CalculatedFields.Expression: return data.totalAcwCount && (data.totalAcwTime / data.totalAcwCount)

CalculatedFields.Name: Average Hold Time - Voice
CalculatedFields.Expression: return data.totalHoldCount && (data.totalHoldTime / data.totalHoldCount)

CalculatedFields.Name: Average Handle Time - Voice
CalculatedFields.Expression: return data.totalHandleCount && (data.totalHandleTime / data.totalHandleCount)

CalculatedFields.Name: Average Not Responding Time
CalculatedFields.Expression: return data.totalNotRespondingCount && (data.totalNotRespondingTime / data.totalNotRespondingCount)

CalculatedFields.Name: Total Handled
CalculatedFields.Expression: return data.totalHandleCount + data.totalHandleCountChat + data.totalHandleCountEmail + data.totalHandleCountMessage

FactTooltips.Name: ACD Status
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The agent's current routing status
FactTooltips.UseTip:
Off-Queue: Not on queue
Idle: Waiting for an interaction
Interacting: Handing an interaction (live or wrap up)
Communicating: On a non-ACD interaction
Not Responding: An interaction alerted the user but they didn't answer before the timeout

FactTooltips.Name: ACD Status Duration
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The amount of time since the agent entered their current routing status

FactTooltips.Name: Secondary Status
FactTooltips.Tooltip: The agent's current presence (Offline, Available, On-Queue, Meeting, etc)

FactTooltips.Tooltip: The amount of time since the agent entered their current presence state
